	(42, 0, 8, 'Up to Date with Submissions', 'up-to-date-with-submissions', '<p>The Joomla Resource Directory team is up to date with everyone that has submitted a listing to the directory.Â  What does this mean exactly?</p>\r\n<p>When the JRD was relaunched it was decided that rather than simply rolling all of the listings from the old directory into the new, everyone would be required to resubmit their information.Â  While creating additional work, it was a unique opportunity to "refresh" all of the information, purge any out of date information, and make sure everyone was conforming to standards for community involvement and trademark compliance.</p>\r\n<p>The practical impact of the decision to start fresh was that hundreds of applications needed to be screened in a relatively short window.Â  It took several months, but late last night a dedicated group of volunteers pushed through the last outstanding application.</p>\r\n<p>If you submitted an applicaiton and your organization is not listed, please check to see if we sent you information on what in your application should be updated or corrected.Â  If you have not heard from us or feel there is an error, please open a ticket at <a href="http://resources.joomla.org/en/do-you-need-help" target="_blank">the JRD help desk</a>.</p>\r\n<p>I want to give a special thank you to <a href="joomlers/jessica-dunbar">Jessica Dunbar</a> for helping plan and implement redirects to maintain SEO from the old directory.</p>\r\n<p>I especially want to thank everyone on the JRD team that took extra time to help with huge initial surge of applications.Â  In the last two weeks there was an exceptional special effort from <a href="joomlers/dawn-russell">Dawn</a>, <a href="joomlers/ron-van-schaik">Ron</a>, <a href="joomlers/chad-windnagle">Chad</a>, Erico, <a href="joomlers/duke-speer">Duke</a>, and <a href="joomlers/soren-beck-jensen">SÃ¸ren</a> (apologies to anyone I am missing).</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 592, '2015-01-21 16:06:47', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(43, 0, 34, '21st-Jan-2015, System Test Team ', '21st-jan-2015-system-test-team', '<p>6th Meeting for Automated Testing working Group,</p>\r\n<p>Meeting was attended by:</p>\r\n<p>Puneet Kala, Javier Gomez, Robert Deutz, Kshitij Sharma, David Jardin, Milton Bryant</p>\r\n<p>Topics Covered in the Meeting:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Kshitij Sharma, informed about the status of System Tests, and updates on the GSOC Project work. System Tests would be updated and merged in next few weeks.</li>\r\n<li>David Jardin and Robert presented the progress that they have made running system tests on Docker Containers, All the progress that has been made is present hereÂ <a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-systemtest-env">https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-systemtest-env</a>Â , Currently the Tests are running on local, by next meeting David and Robert will integrate them to Jenkins.</li>\r\n<li>Javier and Puneet are going to work on writing tests for weblinks in Codeception.Â </li>\r\n<li>Kshitij Will continue helping inÂ documentationÂ alongÂ withÂ ValerieÂ :Â <a href="https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception">https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception</a><a href="https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception"></a></li>\r\n<li><a href="https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception"></a>Javier and Milton will work together on integrating JIRA on Glip chat group for Automated testing.</li>\r\n<li>Robert will Invite members from all the testing groups on Slack/Glip into one.</li>\r\n<li>Javier will rename the working group on volunteer portal</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Next meeting is planned to happen on 4th Feb, 2015 at</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?msg=Joomla+System+Testing+Group+Meeting&amp;iso=20150121T15&amp;p1=%3A&amp;ah=1">http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?msg=System+Tests+working+group+meeting&amp;iso=20150204T15&amp;ah=1</a></p>\r\n<p>Complete Notes for todays meeting can be found here:</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1bpdAlnIyTGU_ByIai8zB45T5ypqUb_P-Tvnjx0UZ6iA/edit">https://docs.google.com/document/d/1bpdAlnIyTGU_ByIai8zB45T5ypqUb_P-Tvnjx0UZ6iA/edit</a><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1_GJqcOYBuBUNHUnDfIYXNBegfAm2rq0NBBWkpd44_0U/edit"></a></p>\r\n<p>Â </p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 525, '2015-01-21 00:00:00', 525, '2015-01-21 17:21:53', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
