argin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Three appendices were added:</span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">A list of the Unified Chart of Accounts (this is the basis for our accounting system).</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">A list of Contributors (people who helped write the document and provided written comments).</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">A list of changes</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The spelling and grammar was also proofed, and the copy modified for readability.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The FiT team will provide a copy of the policy to the board of Open Source Matters for approval.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Day 3, 27-Sep-2015</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Finished second draft of Financial Policy.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">2016 Budget Prep</span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We discussed at length improvements that could be made to the budgeting process (many of these items were added to the Financial Policy document).</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">For the 2016 budget, we will:</span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">provide a form for inputting budget totals, line item owners, Summaries and descriptions.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Each submission will include a detailed budget breakdown, not just a single number for the entire line item.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Budget will have to provide some allowance for the new department-based structure due to be implemented in 2016. </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Expense approval workflow R&amp;D</span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Expense approvals right now are mostly done ad-hoc with no submitted documentation.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">A standardized workflow is needed to:</span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Streamline approvals</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Provide accountability for line item owners </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Improve the reimbursement workflow.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Allow others to process reimbursements and other payments when the person or people with banking access are unavailable.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Martijn prepared an excellent white paper on our needs:</span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qhk7fRVlM3XYP5oSLhP9VTdRgE3E14F58vNuKdmVIoE/edit" style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qhk7fRVlM3XYP5oSLhP9VTdRgE3E14F58vNuKdmVIoE/edit</span></a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Based on these requirements, Martijn explored a number of options, with </span><a href="https://www.expensify.com/pricing" style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Extensify</span></a><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> looking like a good solution.</span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The service is existing so we don&rsquo;t have to invent the wheel</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">It has an automated approval workflow.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">It has automated payment following approval.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Unlimited user activity, but per active user pricing.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Automated currency conversion.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Integration with our accounting software (QuickBooks).</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Digital Receipt Scanning.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Excellent transparency and reporting</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Martijn will match requirements with Expensify features and report back. If it does meet all requirements Martijn will request budget for implementing this service for our projects reimbursement workflow.</span></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 509, '2015-11-13 17:21:00', 509, '2015-11-15 15:25:47', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(142, 0, 34, 'Report of the Automated Testing Code Sprint 2015', 'report-of-the-automated-testing-code-sprint-2015', '<p>This report contains a list of tasks done by the individuals that participated in the Automated Testing Code Sprint that took place in the city of Karlsruhe (Germany) from October 29th until November 1st. More details will be published at the Joomla Magazine on Decembers edition.</p>\r\n<p>Stats:</p>\r\n<p><img src="/images/volunteers/automated-testing-working-group/Screen_Shot_2015-11-16_at_18.48.18.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015 11 16 at 18.48.18" /></p>\r\n<p><img src="/images/volunteers/automated-testing-working-group/Screen_Shot_2015-11-16_at_18.48.26.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015 11 16 at 18.48.26" /></p>\r\n<p><img src="/images/volunteers/automated-testing-working-group/Screen_Shot_2015-11-16_at_18.48.34.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015 11 16 at 18.48.34" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Michael Bodnarchuck (Davert)</h2>\r\n<p>Michael did a training for the participants about general concepts in testing and the usage of Codeception testing framework. Slides are available at:</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1M1D4rPkTU9MTvcIx_wrCvA2MF82nrHw6EUJ_cqptqdE/edit?usp=sharing">https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1M1D4rPkTU9MTvcIx_wrCvA2MF82nrHw6EUJ_cqptqdE/edit?usp=sharing</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Javier Gomez</h2>\r\n<p>- Refactored the tests in weblinks to standardise them</p>\r\n<p>- Created the test scenarios in text format</p>\r\n<p>- Investigated about the usage of the Recorder Codeception extension to document the tests <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/issues/159">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/issues/159 </a>&nbsp;(see video)</p>\r\n<p>- Fix bug in Travis CI builds using PHP 5.3 instead of the selected PHP version in .travis.yml (thanks tito). <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/115">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/115</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- worked on a error reporter when an error is identified in the tests</p>\r\n<p>- generate the task list</p>\r\n<p>- tested PRs and and merges</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Francesco Abeni</h2>\r\n<p>- Improved RoboFile with a local configuration file and some additional behaviours: <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/104">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/104</a> , <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/107">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/107</a> , <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/124">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/124 </a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Fixed a bug in weblinks component, discovered thanks to the automated tests: <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/153">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/153 </a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Improved RoboFile with environments and named based options: <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/158">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/158 </a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Add two new tests for hits counter: <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/127">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/127 </a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Coordinate the task list</p>\r\n<p>- Checked and tested several PRs</p>\r\n<p>- Tried unsuccessfully to convert the team to the use of the timebox technique :-)</p>\r\n<p>- Ate too much :-)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Niels Braczek</h2>\r\n<p>Currently, Joomla is missing integration (functional) tests. This lack is an obstacle for the development of Joomla!4, because there&rsquo;s no feedback on, where backward compatibility is touched. To resolve that, and because the Automated Testing Working Group has decided to use CodeCeption for system tests, I moved the current unit tests to CodeCeption (in joomla-pythagoras repository) as a preparation. The test results seem not to be identical, so this has to be investigated and can and will be fixed later. However, CodeCeption seems to be the way to go, especially, since support for behavioral tests using Gherkin in CodeCeption are on the horizon.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The JBuild Robo.li tool by Yves has been moved (forked) to joomla-projects/jorobo, where it will be extended to be a full fledged build and test tool. My pull request PR#4 contains the quality assurance part of that tool. It generates a lot of metrics reports.</p>\r\n<p>- checkstyle.xml</p>\r\n<p>- pdepend-jdepend.svg</p>\r\n<p>- pdepend-jdepend.xml</p>\r\n<p>- pdepend-pyramid.svg</p>\r\n<p>- pdepend-summary.xml</p>\r\n<p>- phpcpd.xml</p>\r\n<p>- phploc.xml</p>\r\n<p>- phpmd.xml</p>\r\n<p>- phpmetrics.html</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Most of them are well-known already, but phpmetrics.html may be new to many. It is an HTML report with nice diagrams, showing many aspects of the code quality:</p>\r\n<p><img src="/images/volunteers/automated-testing-working-group/2015codesprint/Screen_Shot_2015-11-16_at_18.51.38.png" alt="Screen Shot 2015 11 16 at 18.51.38" /></p>\r\n<p>jorobo will be available and recommended for general Joomla! extension development, when it is released.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Robert Deutz</h2>\r\n<p>- Installed Drone.io on one of our server and configured my weblinks fork to run tests on drone</p>\r\n<p>- Find out that drone is not as stable as we need it for testing Joomla and Weblinks</p>\r\n<p>- We faced a situation that looks at the first try that codeception wasn&rsquo;t working as expected. Checked the situation we with on the issue reduced code and finally found that codeception is doing well.</p>\r\n<p>- Helped to create the jorobo package</p>\r\n<p>- Fix current issue when creating a category in weblinks</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Niels N&uuml;bel</h2>\r\n<p>- Helped Yves to create the jorobo package ( <a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/jorobo">https://github.com/joomla-projects/jorobo</a> &nbsp;)</p>\r\n<p>- Test PRs in github</p>\r\n<p>- Worked on creating a release script for github</p>\r\n<p>- Helped Robert setting up drone.io&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Worked on a automated Release tool</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Yves Hoppe</h2>\r\n<p>- Worked on integrating the new robo.li based build system JoRobo (based on jBuild)</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://compojoom.com/blog/entry/jorobo-tools-for-joomla-development">https://compojoom.com/blog/entry/jorobo-tools-for-joomla-development</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Improvements in Joomla-Browser and Weblinks</p>\r\n<p>- Tested PRs</p>\r\n<p>- Helping Robert setting up drone.io</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/166">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/166</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Integrated new folder structure for Weblinks</p>\r\n<p>- Helping on running tests on all platforms</p>\r\n<p>- Refactoring and improving RoboFile</p>\r\n<p>- 1st level technical pc support ;)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Viktor Vogel</h2>\r\n<p>- Worked on improving the descriptions for Windows machines</p>\r\n<p>- Rewrote the readme file with exact instructions for Windows users</p>\r\n<p>- Made sure that the build command to generate AcceptanceTester on Windows machines are running properly</p>\r\n<p>- Tested and merged PR&rsquo;s in the Weblinks repository <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/commits/master?author=Kubik-Rubik">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/commits/master?author=Kubik-Rubik</a></p>\r\n<p>- Tested and merged PR&rsquo;s by Niels in the jorobo repository <a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/jorobo/commits/master?author=Kubik-Rubik">https://github.com/joomla-projects/jorobo/commits/master?author=Kubik-Rubik</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Improved code styles for JoomlaBrowser regarding Joomla! Coding Standards (see: <a href="http://joomla.github.io/coding-standards/">http://joomla.github.io/coding-standards/</a> ) &nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-browser">https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-browser</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Created the masterpiece of &ldquo;Thug Life Javier&rdquo; - <a href="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/CSqdeioWIAEHz4H.jpg">https://pbs.twimg.com/media/CSqdeioWIAEHz4H.jpg</a> &nbsp;- <a href="https://twitter.com/viktorvogel/status/660781722099974144">https://twitter.com/viktorvogel/status/660781722099974144</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Posted pictures and updates on social channels</p>\r\n<p>- Provided food and shelter for all participants</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Puneet Kala</h2>\r\n<p>- Refactored codeception tests in com_weblinks</p>\r\n<p>- Added several new tests like deleting, moving to Trash, validating tabs on edit view.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Updated Joomla! Browser to add more generic functions like setFilter, clickToolBarButton etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Updated the Robo File in com_weblinks to add functionality to run individual method from a particular test.</p>\r\n<p>- Finalized structure of tests with codeception.</p>\r\n<p>- Modified function in Joomla! browser to work with different screen resolution, so tests could be executed on Mobile, Desktop, Tabs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Kshitij Sharma</h2>\r\n<p>- Created function to kill selenium:&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/116">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/116</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Created archive category tests in AdministratorCategoryCest.php&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/105">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pull/105</a></p>\r\n<p>- I worked on creating the tests for Multilingual Joomla</p>\r\n<p>- Created tests to check the language translation on the front end</p>\r\n<p>- Created category with different languages</p>\r\n<p>- Built function to make an association between the categories</p>\r\n<p>- Worked on writing integration tests of menu items, Weblink Category and Weblinks</p>\r\n<p>- Create a menu item: Displays a list of Web Links for a category</p>\r\n<p>- Submit a Web Link</p>\r\n<p>- Worked on writing functions to delete menuItems, create weblinks with user specified category</p>\r\n<p>- I wrote function in the step files in category.php to publish and unpublish a category</p>\r\n<p>in weblink.php to delete a weblink</p>\r\n<p>- I wrote test to check publish and unpublish feature of category.</p>\r\n<p>- publish a category in backend and then check its existence in front-end</p>\r\n<p>- unpublishing a category in backend and then verifying that it is not present in the front-end.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Issues Reported:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- com_category Error while using modal for making multilingual associations between the categories&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/8231">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/8231</a></p>\r\n<p>Association tab not working in banners&nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/8231">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/8231</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Daniel Dimitrov</h2>\r\n<p>as Victor and I were the only Windows users at the event we spent a lot of our time making sure that the tests can run on Windows Operating System. We\'ve updated the documentation and fixed several bugs that were preventing the tests to work as easily on Windows as they do on other OS systems.</p>\r\n<p>- <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed+author%3Acompojoom">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/pulls?q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed+author%3Acompojoom</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- <a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-browser/pulls?q=is%3Aclosed+is%3Apr+author%3Acompojoom">https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-browser/pulls?q=is%3Aclosed+is%3Apr+author%3Acompojoom</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/wiki/Programs-needed-on-Windows-to-get-the-tests-running">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks/wiki/Programs-needed-on-Windows-to-get-the-tests-running</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Inspected the output of the Selenium Server and tried to find out why sometimes exceptions are thrown</p>\r\n<p>worked on improving the chosen select function tests</p>\r\n<p>- looked at the possibilities of using the Selenium IDE together with the codeception formatter for writing tests faster <a href="https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception#Thoughts_on_Selenium_IDE_and_the_codeception_Formatter">https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception#Thoughts_on_Selenium_IDE_and_the_codeception_Formatter</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 527, '2015-11-16 00:00:00', 527, '2015-11-18 12:34:33', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(143, 41, 0, 'AMP Introduction Meeting November 13 2015', 'amp-introduction-meeting-november-13-2015', '<h2>AMP Introduction Meeting</h2>\r\n<p>Meeting to discuss&nbsp;<span style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px; line-height: normal;">mobile in relation to our recent AMP announcement:&nbsp;</span><a href="https://googleblog.blogspot.ie/2015/10/introducing-accelerated-mobile-pages.html" target="_blank" style="color: #1155cc; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px; line-height: normal;">https://<wbr />googleblog.blogspot.ie/2015/<wbr />10/introducing-accelerated-<wbr />mobile-pages.html</a><span style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12.8px; line-height: normal;"></span></p>\r\n<p>Attendees:</p>\r\n<p>Michael Babker - Joomla, Jessica Dunbar - Joomla, George Wilson - Joomla, Jordan Adler - Google</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Introductions</li>\r\n<li>Joomla governance Model</li>\r\n<li>Have you looked at AMP?</li>\r\n<li>Potential challenges to implementing AMP in Joomla</li>\r\n<li>How extensions work in Joomla</li>\r\n<li>How to handle extensions</li>\r\n<li>setting up a jdocument for AMP HTML</li>\r\n<li>thinking about how to make a noop if an extension has no AMP HTML output method if format not found</li>\r\n<li>Joomla\'s HTML View</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Next steps: </strong></p>\r\n<p>George, Michael, Jess to think about how to develop an AMP HTML output format, and start engaging the community</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 522, '2015-11-16 22:17:13', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(144, 0, 13, '17 November 2015 JUG Team Meeting Minutes', '17-november-2015-jug-team-meeting-minutes', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-569ed8dd-172c-b31a-4ff2-a7e3a034c44a" dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">In attendance:</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Jenn Gress</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Ruth Cheesely</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Saurabh Shah</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Bruce Valle</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Duke Speer</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Djamel Kherbi</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Eric Lamy</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Brian R&oslash;nnow</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Rowan Hoskyns-Abrahall</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Absent:</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Michelle Bisson</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Alejandro Pascoli</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Helvecio da Silva</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Items discussed:</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">1. Discussing Team structure/Team Lead</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">2. Round up on JWC 15, Ruth made a report &nbsp;about is Joomla! In &nbsp;Action session in Bangalore &nbsp;talking about how to organize a JUG, a &nbsp;new JUG came through this session &nbsp;Joomla! User Group Kampala from Uganda and a new JUG in Bangalore is about to be created.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">3. Listing review and pending listing for review, Jenn Gress is reviewing &nbsp;the US JUG , Djamel Kherbi is doing a review of the Asia continent.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">4. Directory review &nbsp;listing, how can people outside &nbsp;the JUG team &nbsp;contribute doing review of the JUG directory.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">5. Task management how we manage the task on the new listing, how to organize the review of the listing by all the members working with the JUG team, how to create a task in Glip.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">6. New TOS approved by CLT, communicate to the user group owner about the new term of condition by email, Rowan will write the message about the new TOS, discussing about the translation of the TOS and the FAQ, and the disclaimer.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">7. JAB16 &nbsp;in Barcelona Spain, making &nbsp;budget for swag and what we want to achieve for the upcoming JAB in Barcelona, preparing goodies packs for the JUG leader.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">8. Discussing New JUG team leader, Ruth will help with the lead until January.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">9. discussing how new contributors get involved, such writing articles for the JCM about the meetings and all the activity related to the JUGS around the world, create a note in jug organizer group chat in Glip to give more information about JUGS activity.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">10.Djamel Kherbi will be the lead on the next JUG meeting on the 1th of December, Duke Speer will do the minute taker.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 468, '2015-11-17 20:41:24', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(145, 3, 0, 'CLT Summit JWC November 2015', 'clt-summit-jwc-november-2015', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-cc426def-51a1-03e2-6531-3b866a94d178" dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38;"><span style="font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Participants:</span><span style="font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;Ruth Cheesley, Peter Bui, Sander Potjer</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38;"><span style="font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; font-weight: bold; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Absent:&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Guillermo Bravo, Alice Grevet</span><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Arial; font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px;">, David Jardin</span><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Arial; font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 1.38; background-color: transparent;"></span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38;"><span style="font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;"></span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38;"><span style="font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Abbreviation Guide:</span></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 14.6667px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.38;"><span styl