	(157, 0, 19, 'Certification Operation Team - Meeting Notes - 10 December, 2015', 'certification-operation-team-meeting-notes-10-dece', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-529c30b2-8c58-d097-3595-43e73715e8cf" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operation Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on December 10th, 2015 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong><em>Presents</em></strong>: Patrick Jungbluth, Sam Suresh, Luca Marzo, Pablo Pantoja, Andre Dreier, Deb Cinkus, Hector Mansilla (partly).</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong><em>Absents</em></strong>: Pamir Masharul Tasbeeh, Arjen Schrijvers, Chris Keen</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team needs several days in order to complete the contract for JLPs</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed about discounts for bulk exams purchase.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">At the launch of the Joomla! Certification Program, until further announcements, all the JLPs will receive a discount to buy exam&rsquo;s seats. No minimum order quantity required, no time expiration for bought seats.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">After 6 months, COT will discuss about minimum order quantity to access the discount.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick and Sam will update certification.joomla.org and exam.joomla.org websites to the new Joomla.org template.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Deb is handling the licensing process for a JIRA Service Desk instance</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca will send an email to all the applicants for JLP after the meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will start processing JLP applications after January, 12</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will ask for a Adobe Echosign access in order to allow JLPs to sign the Contract.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 100 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2015-12-10 14:45:51', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(158, 0, 34, '17th Meeting of Joomla Automated Testing Working Group', '17th-meeting-of-joomla-automated-testing-working-g', '<p>Meeting Date: Wednesday 9th December, 2015</p>\r\n<p><strong>Meeting Attended by:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Puneet Kala, Javier Gomez,&nbsp;Kshitij Sharma, Roger Abt, Yves Hoppe</p>\r\n<p><strong>Absent:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Michael Babker, Niels Braczek, Robert Deutz, Tristan Bailey, Viktor Vogel, Michiel Verhoef, Jack Raknailuang, Valerie Isaksen, Dalpat Singh, Victor Escobar, Tito Alvarez, Milton Bryant, Roland Dalmulder, David Jardin, Prital Patel</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Previous meeting report: </strong></p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-145d4c51-9448-be12-8798-10ce2cb1d21e"><a href="https://magazine.joomla.org/issues/issue-december-2015/item/2912-the-joomla-automated-testing-code-sprint-2015">https://volunteers.joomla.org/reports/142-report-of-the-automated-testing-code-sprint-2015</a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Topics Covered in the meeting:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">## Welcomes and See you laters</p>\r\n<p>Group welcomed our new memeber Prital Patel from Gujarat, India. Prital gave her introduction after the meeting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We all thanked&nbsp;Herv&eacute; Boinnard for his time with the group, he will be in our honour roll from now.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">## Testing Code Sprint</p>\r\n<p>Compelte summary about the work done during the Code Sprint has been published in Joomla! Magazine.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://magazine.joomla.org/issues/issue-december-2015/item/2912-the-joomla-automated-testing-code-sprint-2015">https://magazine.joomla.org/issues/issue-december-2015/item/2912-the-joomla-automated-testing-code-sprint-2015</a><a href="https://magazine.joomla.org/issues/issue-december-2015/item/2912-the-joomla-automated-testing-code-sprint-2015"></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-145d4c51-944e-2b07-be1e-bf31dcc15b3a">## Status of Selenium System Tests at Joomla</span></p>\r\n<p>Puneet, Javier, Kshitij need to work on a strategy to move all the current tests in Selenium to Codeception.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-145d4c51-944f-327b-2bb4-ee1c4f040d89">## JoomlaBrowser</span></p>\r\n<p>A lot of new commits done during the code sprint, Joomla! Browser already download 11242 times on packagist&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://packagist.org/packages/joomla-projects/joomla-browser">https://packagist.org/packages/joomla-projects/joomla-browser</a><a href="https://packagist.org/packages/joomla-projects/joomla-browser"></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">## Documentation (Javier, Kshitij and Valerie)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Documentation at <a href="https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception">https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception</a> needs to be updated with the latest changes at <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks#tests">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks#tests</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">## QA Scripts (Code Style) and others at Jorobo project</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Jorobo is a new Tool and Task based on Robo.li to manage Joomla Extension Development and Releases. It was created during the Code Sprint and is in Alpha stages.: <a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/jorobo">https://github.com/joomla-projects/jorobo</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">## Next meeting</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">18th Automated Testing Team Meeting</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">\r\n<table style="height: 38px;" width="256"><colgroup><col width="624" /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Date &amp; Time</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Wed, Jan 13, 2016 at 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?msg=18th+Meeting+for+Joomla+Automated+Testing+Working+Group&amp;iso=20160113T2030&amp;p1=438&amp;ah=1">http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?msg=18th+Meeting+for+Joomla+Automated+Testing+Working+Group&amp;iso=20160113T2030&amp;p1=438&amp;ah=1</a>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 525, '2015-12-12 00:00:00', 525, '2015-12-12 04:02:49', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(159, 0, 13, 'JUG Team Meeting Report - 1 December 2015', '1-december-2015-jug-team-meeting-report', '<p>Chaired by Djamel, seven members of the JUG Team (listed below) met on December 1, 2015.&nbsp; <br /><br />The primary item of business was the ongoing systematic review of the JUG Directory\'s listings in which assigned team members are reviewing all the listings in a country to verify the JUG is still active, directory links work, and that policies are being followed.<br /><br />The JUG naming policy is a frequent area of community concern and misunderstanding.&nbsp; JUGs being named for an entire country are not allowed.&nbsp; Country-level naming is reserved for country-related translation and localization teams, for major JDay events as approved by the Events team, and for multi-JUG portals that provide equal-access to and event listings for all JUGs in the country or region along with subdomains for each member JUG.<br /><br />Connected with this topic, an updated TOS has been drafted and will be posted to the team for review and comment.<br /><br />Also discussed was the new prospect onboarding process by which those interested in participating as a JUG Team member start out as a JUG Community for a minimum of 3 months to learn the system and complete directory reviews for one or more countries and/or undertake other Team tasks.&nbsp; After learnng the system and demonstrating their availability and willingness, Community members will be considered for Team meber status if they desire making the regular monthly commitment that that entails.<br /><br />Progress is also being made on a rennovation of the Directory software and site.<br /><br />Thank you to those attending:<br />Djamel Kherbi<br />Duke Speer<br />Ruth Cheesley<br />Saurabh Shah<br />Alejandro Pascoli<br />Jenn Gress<br />Rowan Hoskyns Abrahall<br /><br />Unexpected/unexcused absences:<br />Bruce Valle<br />Brian Ronnow<br />Michelle Bisson</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 506, '2015-12-02 00:00:00', 506, '2015-12-15 02:50:15', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(160, 0, 19, 'Certification Operation Team - Meeting Notes - 17 December, 2015', 'certification-operation-team-meeting-notes-17-dece', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-42fb8e13-b056-7d7a-7576-83c9cd43b6b9" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operation Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on December 17th, 2015 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Presents</em></span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Sam Suresh, Luca Marzo, Pablo Pantoja (partly), Andre Dreier, Deb Cinkus.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Absents</em></span>: Pamir Masharul Tasbeeh, Arjen Schrijvers, Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick shared with the Team the Badge drafts for the Certification Program created by the Marketing Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Steering Team will choose the final badges for students and the program.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JLPs could sell exams bundled with training courses.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JLPs can travel to J! Events and do proctoring and they charge extra $ in the exam seat price.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Deb is still handling the licensing process for a JIRA Service Desk instance</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">In the first phase, Joomla! Certification Program will sell seats to JLPs and Event organizers. In the future, Candidates could buy their seat directly.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">No discounts for JLPs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Reasonable extra-charges at Joomla! Events are possible.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JLPs can extra-charge exam price (reasonable). Team will supervise.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team is reviewing the Contracts for JLPs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will ask to access Google Analytics for the certification websites.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will look for volunteers: Exam Translators, Developers, Regional Coordinators.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Application for JLPs and Volunteers will be processed after January, 12 2016.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><em>All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</em></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 85 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2015-12-17 14:29:33', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(161, 41, 0, 'PLT Meeting Thursday December 17th, 2015', 'plt-meeting-thursday-december-17th-2015', '<p>Previous meeting minutes: <a href="reports/120-plt-summit-sptember-2015-meeting-report">https://volunteers.joomla.org/reports/120-plt-summit-sptember-2015-meeting-report</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Present: Javier G&oacute;mez, Robert Deutz, Chris Davenport, Tessa Mero, Viktor Vogel, George Wilson, Marco Dings, Roland Dalmulder, Thomas Hunziker</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Absent: Jessica Dunbar, Tom Hutchison</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Total time of the meeting: &nbsp;2h</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2># Topics:</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>## 3.4.7 Security Release &amp; Marketing, 20 minutes (George)</h3>\r\n<p>A security release will We will be releasing 3.4.7 ~Monday. It will contain b/c breaks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Action items: specific members of the Security Strike team will be contacted to cover exploit opportunities.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>## State of Joomla 4 / UX (Marco)</h3>\r\n<p>Current effort is aimed and getting a base where current contributors can start leading teams iso doing things themselves.</p>\r\n<p>UX is searching for additions to the team with practical UX knowledge.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>## Continuation of terms (Marco)</h3>\r\n<p>While the transition team work continues the PLT decides to continue with term renewals as before. We are planning to add more members to the PLT.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>## 2016 Budget (Robert)</h3>\r\n<p>Action Item: prepare Team Goals for 2016</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>## Release plan for 3.6 (Chris)</h3>\r\n<p>Action Item: a timebox is planned to be created</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>## Timeboxing minor releases ( 3.x )</h3>\r\n<p>Action Items:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Stick to the plan of more frequent and smaller releases</p>\r\n<p>- Document the release process better&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Automate release procedure (Jorobo is a project that was born during the Automated Testing Code sprint. Is a combination of automated tasks for Joomla made in Robo.li Task Runner framework. Is in Alpha stages https://github.com/joomla-projects/jorobo but should be the base for solving tasks like automating the Joomla release.)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 527, '2016-01-07 08:07:04', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(162, 0, 5, 'December 2015 - Events Team Meeting Report', 'december-2015-events-team-meeting-report', '<div><strong>December 9, 2015</strong></div>\r\n<div>Attendees: <strong>Radek Suski, Sigrid Suski, Rowan Hoskyns Abrahall, Carlos C&aacute;mara, David Aswani</strong></div>\r\n<div>Not in attendance:&nbsp;<strong>David Jardin (excused)</strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Discussed following topics:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Joomladay Italy and Joomla Festival problem. We are going to pass this to CLT. They should decide if we remove the events from the Events site</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Update Events Site -&gt; will be updated this weekend by Radek</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Approval Training -&gt; Radek makes a Doodle</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Articles for the Magazine -&gt; David A will take care of it.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Update the SobiPro template for the events site. Assigned to Rowan</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Carlos and David A. are going to add their bio to the Events site</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">We can sponsor&nbsp;events again!</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Adding a new rule to get a financial report from the Joomladay organizers -&gt; next meeting</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">New meeting dates: 12 January 2016, 9 February, 8 March, 5 April &nbsp;@ 17:00 UTC</li>\r\n</ol></div>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 449, '2016-01-11 09:19:32', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(163, 0, 17, 'Report from the Joomla! Certification Steering Team - 12th January 2016', 'report-from-the-joomla-certification-steering-team', '<p><span style="color: #888888; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelveticaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: pre-wrap; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;">The Joomla! Certification Steering Team started into a new year.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #888888; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelveticaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: pre-wrap; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;">In the meeting the team received an overview about the new energy in the Joomla! Certification Marketing Team. Robert Wilson has created a creative and enthusiastic team to start to raise the awareness for the Certification Program in the near future. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #888888; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelveticaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: pre-wrap; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;">To get all the work done the team tries to reactivate members, who have signed up for the team a long time ago and is looking for volunteers to participate as well. Sign in at </span><a href="https://certification.joomla.org/call-for-volunteers" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="color: #729e52; text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelveticaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: pre-wrap; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: #ffffff;">https://certification.joomla.org/call-for-volunteers</a><span style="color: #888888; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelveticaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: pre-wrap; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;"> if you are interested. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #888888; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelveticaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: pre-wrap; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;">The Exam Team, the Operations Team and the Platform Team have worked hard over the holidays and managed to get the platform almost ready. The new Big Mac Index is released, which will be taken as a basis for the charge of the Joomla! Exam. And the number of questions, ready to be answered by the participants, is growing weekly. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #888888; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelveticaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: pre-wrap; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;">To define a new budget for 2016 we expect 350 people taking the exam, which means an income of about $ 14,000.- . Besides that, we need to have a budget to proctor exams at Joomla! Day events, the Joomla! World Conference or other Joomla! meetings like at the Joomla! User Groups. And we need money for marketing purposes like AdWords and Facebook campaigns and print material like brochures, stickers etc. </span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #888888; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelveticaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: auto; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: pre-wrap; widows: 1; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; display: inline !important; float: none; background-color: #ffffff;">The steering group was very happy to see this huge progress over the holidays. </span></p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 766, '2016-01-14 00:00:00', 766, '2016-01-14 13:29:23', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(164, 0, 19, 'Certification Operation Team - Meeting Notes - 14 January, 2016', 'certification-operation-team-meeting-notes-14-janu', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-b6e15e15-4075-93e5-7ea6-5f1c2c3eaf13" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operation Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on January 14th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Presents</em></span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Sam Suresh, Luca Marzo, Johan Van der Velde.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Absents</em></span>: Pamir Masharul Tasbeeh, Arjen Schrijvers, Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Deb Cinkus, Andre Dreier, Pablo Pantoja</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick received access to Adobe Echosign</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team is going to share contracts for JLPs to OSM&rsquo;s President in order to be reviewed by the OSM Legal Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team is creating small working groups to handle different actions: application screening (JLPs / Volunteers / National Coordinators / JUGs &amp; Events).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Contracts for JLPs are currently under review by the Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team defined a quality-focused process to evaluate JLP Applications.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team started screening JLP and volunteers application on January, 12. If you sent an application, please be patient during the screening process.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team is working on marketing materials for JLPs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team will approve the badges for certified administrators and JLPs in few days.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team stated that the Platform completion is at 85%.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Deb is still working on the Service Desk instance.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick will remove inactive team members next days.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 55 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2016-01-14 14:08:55', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(165, 0, 13, '19 January 2016 JUG Team Meeting Minutes ', '19-january-2016-jug-team-meeting-minutes', '<p>In attendance:</p>\r\n<p>Brian Ronnow<br />Djamel Kherbi<br />Jenn Gress</p>\r\n<p>Absent:</p>\r\n<p>Ruth Cheesely<br />Helvecio da Silva<br />Eric Lamy<br />Saurabh Shah<br />Alejandro Pascoli<br />Bruce Valle<br />Rowan Hoskyns-Abrahall<br />Michelle Bisson<br />Duke Speer<br />Marco Richter</p>\r\n<p>With such a small group today we just went over the pending reports and listings. We tabled a number of things that need input from Ruth. Jenn sent an email to Ruth to find out if she is alright - she\'s been out of communication for some time.</p>\r\n<p>Jenn also to connect with a couple of members that have been out of communication for a long time too.</p>\r\n<p>Because of our meeting lead/minute rotation, we made some adjustments based on activity of who is next on the list to lead and take minutes. ;)</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 535, '2016-01-19 19:29:19', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(166, 0, 19, 'Certification Operation Team - Meeting Notes - 21 January, 2016', 'certification-operation-team-meeting-notes-21-janu', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-a773dded-6477-0a1c-1a61-bb3cc88e774a" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operation Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on January 21st, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Presents</em></span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Sam Suresh, Luca Marzo, Pablo Pantoja.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Absents</em></span>: Arjen Schrijvers, Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Deb Cinkus, Andre Dreier, Johan Van der Velde.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team informed team about the badges situation. They will choose the official badge set during next team meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick updated Big Mac Index document and defined the new pricelist for Exam.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Contracts for JLP and Students have been sent to OSM Lawyers for review.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will add new volunteers to improve the screening process of JUGs/JDays applications.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca will draft documents about the JUGs/JDays applications screening process to allow new volunteers to start working quickly.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">A dedicated subteam is already working on JLPs applications. Team is processing each application and sending candidates an email asking for clarifications and documents.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 50 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2016-01-21 13:56:48', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(167, 0, 5, 'January 2016 - Events Team Meeting Report', 'january-2016-events-team-meeting-report', '<p dir="ltr">Attendees: <strong>Radek Suski, Sigrid Suski, &nbsp;David Jardin, Rowan Hoskyns Abrahall, Carlos C&aacute;mara, David Aswani</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Date/Time: January 12, 2016 @ 17:00 UTC</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Topics:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Adding a new rule to get a financial report from the Joomladay organizers. We are going to ask organisers to provide a financial report on their event website and provide a link to the document we can put in their listing on the event website. We can use JaB financial report as an example</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">We confirm the approval training at Thursday at 3 PM UTC</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">We decided to follow the idea with speakers directory on the event website. Carlos is going to help with that.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Budget. We need to ask Victor if we are currently allowed to sponsor events at that time. Until this has been clarified the sponsoring option is still disabled. <strong><em>[edited] Victor confirmed that budget is frozen at the moment and we cannot start offering sponsorship until further notice</em></strong>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">We are going to try to organise meeting at JoomlaDay&trade; UK - document sorted.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">We are asking Rowan to correct the footer at JoomlaDay&trade; UK website - already done.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">Contact Pete about removing the old email addresses.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 449, '2016-01-21 00:00:00', 449, '2016-01-21 14:21:21', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(168, 0, 40, 'Joomla 3.6  webservices', 'joomla-36-webservices', '<p>The webservices workgroup has started to build an architecture that will integrate webservices (digital connectors with other data sources) in Joomla, planned for the release of Joomla 3.6.</p>\r\n<p>The first steps are made to build a first version, based on proven component webservices solutions as well as with involvement of community members working with web-connectivity and Joomla on a daily base.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As security and performance as well as flexibility, standardization are hot topics on this item the workgroup has decided to share a first introduction on this subject thru this writing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Introduction to Webservices</strong></p>\r\n<p>There are already Joomla website that use webservices in:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Webshops that connect with suppliers.</li>\r\n<li>News services bundle content from different sources to enrich there website content.</li>\r\n<li>Portals collect data for its users to process and or create dashboards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Webservices are used in Commercial, Governmental and Educational organizations.</p>\r\n<p>Also there is the &ldquo;Internet of Things&rdquo; which needs webservices to connect application in order to exchange data.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Rapid growth of webservices</strong></p>\r\n<p>Over the last couple of years we have seen a growth in the number of Joomla websites that use webservices and the outlook is that this will increase exponential, as the near future will ask for more and more applications to connect.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Why webservices in Joomla?</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The balance between the framework, CMS and component structure make it very powerful and useful for webservices.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Joomla&rsquo;s great market share in the none-blog, application framework space creates demand for this functionality.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>The last couple of years Joomla websites using applications with integrated webservices have become a fast growing market.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>At this moment most of the developers use the component model to setup a connection. By creating a separate centralized standard docking point Joomla will be able to handle data and instruction in a more flexible way and bring down cost on webservices development and maintenance as well as better manage security.</p>\r\n<p>For those using just the CMS it won&rsquo;t be in there way, for those who want to connect to other CMS platforms or application it&rsquo;s will be ready for use by setting up an entry which will manage the connection.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Progress</strong></p>\r\n<p>- In 2012 a group of people started an initiative to investigate the possibilities of integrating web services in the Joomla Framework architecture in such a way Joomla could improve thru the use of webservices.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>- Medio 2014 development in webservices standards like &ldquo;Rest&rdquo; and architecture models as well as demand from a part of the community, made it a good moment to make a start with the integration in Joomla challenge a separate entry in the architecture for the webservice, option for multiple agents that are easy to configure.</p>\r\n<p>- At J and Beyond in Prague, 2015 a start was made with coding based on an existing solution.</p>\r\n<p>- January 2016 the project is on Github.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Next report</strong></p>\r\n<p>As soon as a first functional installable version is available an update report will follow. If there are people working with webservices and not yet being a part of the workgroup they are more then welcome to join.</p>\r\n<p>To get the latest news join the Glip webservices group. On the upcoming Joomla events there will be presentations.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 1589, '2016-01-22 01:33:57', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(169, 0, 67, 'Meeting notes Joomla.org redesign', 'meeting-notes', '<p>We met in the team and went through the submitted designs and selected various design elements that we liked and a sub team was assigned with combining the elemenmts into a final design.</p>\r\n<p>https://docs.google.com/document/d/1v39ZM2BWEEASkvJ_uRLZgPw93la-62h7VmQlEHUuwsw/edit?usp=sharing</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 488, '2016-01-25 00:00:00', 488, '2016-01-25 11:18:11', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(170, 0, 7, 'MWG LT - Kick Off Meeting 2016', 'lt-kick-off-meeting-2016', '<p>Leadership Kick Off meeting 2016 :</p>\r\n<p>Agenda and notes can be found at :</p>\r\n<p>https://docs.google.com/document/d/1R5WvUekl2xs-jt59PXki5nrKSvCOnx5-YT51XTkTQaw/edit?usp=sharing</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 485, '2016-01-27 00:00:00', 485, '2016-01-27 11:11:34', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(171, 0, 19, 'Certification Operation Team - Meeting Notes - 28 January, 2016', 'certification-operation-team-meeting-notes-28-janu', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-c185a6ff-8899-92d0-22b3-1e3d71fed44c" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operation Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on January 28th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Presents</em></span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Sam Suresh, Luca Marzo, Andre Dreier.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span></em>: Arjen Schrijvers, Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Deb Cinkus, Pablo Pantoja, Johan Van der Velde.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed about a price charge for JLPs when they come to proctor to a JUG/Joomla Event exam session.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team sent contracts for JLPs and Students to the OSM&rsquo;s Legal Team for a final review and approval.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will publish on the Certification website the price list for 2016. The price indicates the actual exam price according to Big Mac Index. Joomla! Learning Partners may offer additional services or bundled training subject to additional costs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Joomla! trusted volunteers could serve as proctors at Joomla Events exam sessions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Updates from the <strong>Certification Platform Team</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">CPT will contact the hosting provider directly about hosting matters.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">CPT working on 3 new features in the platform</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">New Target to ready new site by 30th January 2016 and first test exam by 4th February.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 65 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2016-01-28 14:29:00', 669, '2016-01-28 14:31:15', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(172, 0, 44, 'JED Team Meeting Notes - 29th January, 2016', 'jed-team-meeting-notes-29th-january-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-eb5084e7-8dc8-74a6-b99f-3e4d10d4b825" dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Today the Joomla Extensions Directory (JED) team met at 6:00 AM (GMT -8) via Glip to discuss our progress of current tasks.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Statistics for the month of January 2016:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Listings: 292 Submitted 266 Approved</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Tickets: 513 Submitted 479 Processed </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Reviews: 1245 Submitted</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Jira Updates</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">We have updated the several hundred pending Jira issues to make sure they are up to date and still a bug. We haven&rsquo;t been able to work with any issues since we have been waiting on contract approvals and signatures most of 2015 to be able to move forward.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">There are many bug fixes waiting in the queue to be pushed to the live server. Rob (the previous JED developer) is tasked today to work with the JED team on board with this. It is a manual task on the Jenkins server.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">By the next February meeting, we should be adding statistics to our bug fixes.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Updated JED Template</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">The updated JED template is done. Thanks to Markus Bopp and Miron Savan. It is now waiting to be pushed to the live server. :-)</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Developer Chat</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">To gain access to the developer chat, send an email to tessa.mero (at) extensions.joomla.org. You will see important tasks to the right, and we will discuss general issues there. (Specific issues will be discussed within Jira). Also, Jira integrates with our chat system, so you can easily see new issues and replies to issues right in our chat system.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">JEDChecker</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Jaz will have things up and running in the next few weeks by the next JED team meeting. We will have great news about our new updated JEDChecker. To view our plans with the JEDChecker, please check out our last team meeting report at the link on the far bottom.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Community Support</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top