nt-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Online</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Recorder: </span><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Britta Stender</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">In Attendance:</span><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> TJ Baker, Ronni Christiansen, Britta Stender, Mathias Jensen, Mike Demopoulos, Matt Lenning</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Not present:</span><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">, Brian Peat, Jerri Christiansen</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.62; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Agenda:</span></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; margin-left: 25px;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Todos from last meeting</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-d9836e91-72af-8de2-ad3d-a57a593fe2a9" style="font-weight: normal;"><br /><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We didn&rsquo;t get an agenda up prior to this meeting, however, the purpose was mainly to follow up on our todo list. The team agreed to rotate responsibility for the Agenda. Britta will make sure to get the next one up 2-3 days before the next meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The new sponsor packages got approved by the treasurer, Ronni, and the rest of the team. Mathias will design new icons for Mike to use in the print material.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Possible keynote speakers have been contacted. We are pending answer from most of them. 2 speakers have confirmed, 2 have declined as they are not available.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Ronni and TJ briefly mentioned the pros and cons for JWC17. TJ and Ronni will continue their research and present a finalised pros and cons list at the next meeting</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We welcomed Matt Lenning to the team. TJ and Matt will take a quick call some other day to get him set up. Matt will have a look at the proposed theme ideas and make a suggestion at the next meeting. </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Currently there is no marketing plan. The previous years marketing have been very loose / on the fly. So the first task for Matt to start working on would be a plan.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">TJ and Ronni have reviewed and approved Mike&rsquo;s budget for hosting con. Mike will be presenting a two hour workshop.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">There has been no progress on the design for the new website. Britta and Mathias will try to get some done the following week. We will have to check up with Jerri on the progress. Deadline should be before JAB and not the 24th.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Todo:</span></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Britta: Set up agenda</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Mathias: Deliver new sponsor icons for Mike</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Britta + Mathias: Finish the design asap</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Jerri: Website implementation deadline May 24th, preferably earlier.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Ronni + TJ: Finish pros and cons list for JWC17 locations</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">TJ + Matt: Will meet and get him set up</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Jerri: Research which component to use for the programme at the website</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Jerri: Contact volunteers regarding a conference app</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Review the AV purchase suggestions prepared by Brian</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.656; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All: Theme decision postponed till next meeting.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 515, '2016-05-02 00:00:00', 515, '2016-05-02 17:18:25', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(230, 0, 21, 'TLWG Meeting Report - May 04, 2016', 'tlwg-meeting-report-may-04-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-1586d1fa-7d95-61a4-af3c-9dee0016577d" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Trademark &amp; Licensing Working Group (TLWG) meets once a month. This meeting was held on May 4th, 2016 at 10.00 p.m. (CET) on Glip.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Presents</strong>: Marco Richter, Marijke Stuivenberg, Luca Marzo, Jenn Gress.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Absents</strong>: Deb Cinkus, Duke Speer, Victor Drover, Wilmar Meijer</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team opened a call for volunteers in mid April and just 4 applications received. Team will keep the call open for the current month.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Trademark &amp; Licensing Working Group needs motivated volunteers that, after a short training, will be able to process tasks.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will improve the application form, to better explain what team is looking for.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will interview the actual applicants via email.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed on how to process trademark logo/domain violations. A &ldquo;How to process violations&rdquo; document is being arranged for that.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed also about the policy to process creativity compliance with trademark rules.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will start to meet twice a month.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 65 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2016-05-04 21:04:15', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(231, 0, 19, 'Certification Operations Team - Meeting Notes - 5 May, 2016', 'certification-operation-team-meeting-notes-5-may-2', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-e7e6e7f6-80fc-edf5-e8ca-92f6c9d9e65a" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on May 5th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Luca Marzo, Todd Woodward.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Deb Cinkus, Johan Van der Velde, Sam Suresh, Arjen Schrijvers, Pablo Pantoja, Richard Van Tilborg, Andre Dreier.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca reported news from the Steering Meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team finalized questions and provided them to Sam, in order to be uploaded on the Joomla! Exam Platform. Operations Team would say a very big &ldquo;Thank you&rdquo; to all the people in Exam and Platform Teams for their big work during last days.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">We should start the Pilot Test by the end of this week</span>.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Steering Meeting confirmed the intention to have the first Community Certification Event at JandBeyond, in Barcelona (20-22 May 2016).</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick contacted JRD Team Leader and they will have a call next days to define the process to have Joomla! Learning Partners listed on Joomla! Resource Directory.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team is working on a simple &ldquo;Agreement&rdquo; for JUGs and JEvents that will host exams.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will work on a process for Travel Funding applications.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Last week Luca trained Johan, Todd and Pablo on how to handle and process RC applications.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Johan, Todd and Pablo are working on applications from Regional Coordinators candidates and started the screening and evaluation process.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca completed the screening process of all the applications from Joomla! Learning Partners candidates and JUG/JEvents.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Most of the applicants did not answer our email and/or tickets, so we cannot process their applications. If you applied as JLP or you asked to host a Certification Exam, please look at your mailbox and answer emails from the Certification program. If you did not received email from us, please open a support ticket at <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/support">https://certification.joomla.org/support</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 50 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Applications Summary</h3>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Joomla! Learning Partners</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Total applications: 48</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Ready to sign: 18.8%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">On-hold: 10.4%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Interviewed: 4.2 %</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Withdrawn: 6.3%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rejected: 6.3%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Pending (waiting for answers): 54.2%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Leading countries (overall): Germany, Italy, United States.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Joomla! User Groups / Joomla! Events</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Total applications: 13</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Applications from JUGs: 84.6%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Applications from JEvents: 15.4%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">In progress (waiting for answers): 69.2%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Waiting interview/agreement: 15.4%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rejected: 15.4% (They was events that already took place)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Leading countries (overall): Germany, United States.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2016-05-05 15:00:00', 669, '2016-05-06 12:20:29', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(232, 0, 60, 'Joomla!X News, Week 18', 'joomlax-news-week-18', '<p>The <strong>Doctrine storage handler</strong> is making progress (<a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-pythagoras/pull/85/files">PR#85</a>).</p>\r\n<p>Development of the first <strong>horizontal component</strong> (<a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-pythagoras/compare/feature/doctrine...feature/workflow">Workflow</a>) has started. It will add a state field (publish, unpublish, archive, trash, publish_up, and publish_down) to a vertical component.</p>\r\n<p>For the creation of <strong>API and CLI</strong> entry points, a test environment was set up using Docker and Behat. It will get published after the Behat tests have been moved to the new Codeception 2.2, which now also supports Gherkin (an executable feature description language).</p>\r\n<h2>Templates First</h2>\r\n<p>The Architecture Group agreed on, that it would be nice to present something more visual in Barcelona (Spain). It would improve the acceptance of the clean base approach, if it was able to demonstrate the support of Bootstrap 4 and another framework, for example Foundation.</p>\r\n<p>Because there are only two weeks left until J and Beyond, it is not possible to have both API/CLI and templating in a presentable state for the conference. Since there is a great interest from the community in support of different Javascript frameworks, the team decided to give it a higher priority, and to postpone the API and CLI access until after JaB.</p>\r\n<h2>Informal Gathering</h2>\r\n<p>We are planning an informal gathering on Thursday afternoon or evening to showcase, discuss and educate. If you are interested, please contact Niels Braczek or Marco Dings via the portal or Glip. We will then send you an invitation with the details, once we have figured out where and when exactly.</p>\r\n<p>The Joomla! 4 Architecture Team</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 625, '2016-05-05 16:14:25', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(233, 0, 39, 'JUX Team Report May 6th 2016 ', 'jux-team-report-may-6th-2016', '<p>Over the past month we\'ve had several meetings and collaborated with several other working groups. With the recent changes in the release schedule and J &amp; Beyond coming quickly, our primary focus right now is research and planning, along with team administration. Our hope is that our progress and findings will generate more community support for our efforts at the J &amp; Beyond conference.</p>\r\n<p>Due to the overwhelming response to our team efforts and call for volunteers, we are still sorting through applications and task outlines. We want to add many new contributors to the team sooner than later, but we also and want to ensure it is easy for the new people to get started so our time is well spent. The amount of administrative time and effort this process would take was severely underestimated, mainly due to overwhelming interest and research participation. We are doing our best to get this sorted out and get our new contributors involved. We thank everyone for their patience.</p>\r\n<p>We have a lot share and lot more coming soon, details are below</p>\r\n<h3>JUX April 2016 Survey Results</h3>\r\n<p>Our initial survey went well, with over 500 responses around 200 volunteers for more research over a 2 week period. The goal of this survey was not only to collect general information about Joomla usage, it was also to find more volunteers. Both goals were accomplished. The data we obtained is very general but it paints a picture we can learn from and use for more detailed research.</p>\r\n<p>Big thanks to Chris Raymond and Eric Fernance for their efforts on the survey and our research efforts in general, they have done a great job. And big thanks to everyone who participated in the survey.</p>\r\n<p>We have the raw data to share and some basic insights and recommendations. A more detailed analysis is in progress and we will be following up with all volunteers shortly.</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://developer.joomla.org/cms/user-experience/645-jux-may-2016-update.html" target="_blank">Raw survey data and initial analysis can be found here.</a></p>\r\n<h3>J35 Survey Launch</h3>\r\n<p>We are launching our new survey this week. It is specifically targeted to gather feedback about the Joomla 3.5 release. We will share initial data near the time of the J &amp; Beyond conference near the end of May.</p>\r\n<h3>Team Updates</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Joomla 3 efforts:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Joomla 3 Administrative project has been gathering research over the past month and discussing the most effective and realistic changes to recommend and develop. With the recent change in the release schedule, we\'re not entirely sure how our efforts fit into the big picture. Little information has been provided to us regarding this.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks to Brian Peat, Tony Partridge and Jason Nickerson for all their help and suggestions.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks to all of our users in the LinkedIn Joomla User Group for fueling some very active discussions regarding the Joomla 3 administrator area. We\'ve gathered an enormous amount of feedback and insight from these threads. These two discussions can be found here:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/groups/52867/52867-6121774224836227076" target="_blank">LinkedIn J3 Administrator Discussion</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/groups/52867/52867-6126069637944791041" target="_blank">LinkedIn J3 Dashboard Discussion</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Regional Team Updates</h3>\r\n<p>Huge thanks to Niranjan Janardhana. A few weeks ago we decided to form a regional team in Asia to help with time zone and communication issues and Niranjan has made much progress and gotten new contributors involved. This seems to be a great way to overcome a few of the logistical challenges we face in a global community. We\'ve been able to more involve people in the process and get more done as a result.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Niranjan\'s report:</strong></p>\r\n<p>We have collected feedback and research from a number of users as part of Installation and onboarding survey. Our goal is to provide a user friendly and welcoming installation experience within an inviting and helpful atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p><strong>JUX Onboarding Program</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Through team information survey, we got considerable insight on below for the members</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>the timezone of the team member</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>their preferred mode of collaboration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>their wider area of interest in JUX projects</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>their core interest and passion</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This information was then interpolated with all the JUX project backlog items. This resulted in a matrix identifying best fit resources for JUX projects.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Regional Team Program</strong></p>\r\n<p>We made considerable progress in addressing extreme time zones and language differences. Due to this initiative,</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>the regional lead was approachable for queries of team members during their timezone.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>we now have 24x7 access to JUX leadership on Glip: US timezone is covered by Cliff and Asia timezone is covered by Niranjan.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The availability of Region lead also helped in conducting Google hangout with regional members in the regional accent</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Niranjan approaced few additional volunteers in the Asia region and their onboarding is in progress.</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Henry Nguyen has expressed his interest in Admin template project. He did demo of the JoomlaShine PowerAdmin and PageBuilder extension. Henry has immense experience in templates and the above JoomlaShine offerings have several capabilities that are planned for implementation in Joomla4 admin template.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Joomla 4 Progress</strong></p>\r\n<p>The documentation of core elements in pattern library is nearing completion. This will be common reference document for both Architecture team and UX team. Henry has also agreed to collaborate on the pattern library.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;We are looking forward to the JAB conference. We know many conversations and connections will be made there and we\'re also hoping for more collaboration between teams. For now, we\'re gathering all the user data we can to propose the changes at the conference we believe will benefit our users, our community and our platform the most. - Cliff Pfeifer JUX Team Lead</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 673, '2016-05-07 00:00:00', 673, '2016-05-07 22:59:36', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(234, 0, 53, 'Informal May Meeting', 'informal-may-meeting', '<p>Several issues were discussed during the recent code cleanup sprint in Manchester.</p>\r\n<p>We decided not to proceed any further with the idea to change the terminology for ACL and Viewing Levels as it is too big a change after all these years.</p>\r\n<p>Peter Martin suggested that we produce a guideline for structured naming of language variables and we will work on this over the next few weeks.</p>\r\n<p>During JAB it is intended to have a make it happen session to review the search tooltips and hopefully some other areas.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 448, '2016-05-10 08:55:24', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(235, 0, 19, 'Certification Operations Team - Meeting Notes - 12 May, 2016', 'certification-operations-team-meeting-notes-12-may', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-b04f63cb-a520-1d00-7ba1-4ee995869491" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operation Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on May 12th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Todd Woodward, Richard van Tilborg, Pablo Pantoja, Hector Mansilla.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Chris Keen, Deb Cinkus, Johan Van der Velde, Sam Suresh, Arjen Schrijvers, Andre Dreier.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca reported news from the Steering Meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team members took the Exam Pilot Test until May 10 and sent feedbacks to Sam about the user experience on the Platform.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Grade to pass the Joomla! Administrator Exam is 80%.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team is working on a landing page template to promote Exam sessions at JoomlaDay and Joomla!-related events. We&rsquo;ll provide this template (HTML code + Images) to approved sessions organizers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Johan, Todd and Pablo are working on applications from Regional Coordinators candidates and started the screening and evaluation process.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Richard shared with the team a preview of the Certificate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed about the JLP Welcome Pack and the possibility to add a quick Learning Guide.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Most of the applicants did not answer our email and/or tickets, so we cannot process their applications. If you applied as JLP or you asked to host a Certification Exam, please look at your mailbox and answer emails from the Certification program. If you did not received email from us, please open a support ticket at <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/support">https://certification.joomla.org/support</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Next team meeting will be on May 26, 2016.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 65 minutes.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Applications Summary</h3>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Joomla! Learning Partners</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Total applications: 49</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Ready to sign: 20.4%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">On-hold: 10.2%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Interviewed: 6.1 %</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Withdrawn: 6.1%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rejected: 6.1%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Pending (waiting for answers): 51%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Leading countries (overall): Germany, Italy, United States.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Joomla! User Groups / Joomla! Events</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Total applications: 14</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Applications from JUGs: 78.6%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Applications from JEvents: 21.4%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">In progress (waiting for answers): 71.4%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Waiting interview/agreement: 14.3%</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rejected: 14.3% (They was events that already took place)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Leading countries (overall): Germany, United States.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2016-05-12 15:00:00', 669, '2016-05-12 13:23:06', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(236, 0, 13, '17th May 2016 JUG Team Meeting Minutes', '17th-may-2016-jug-team-meeting-minutes', '<p dir="ltr"><strong>In attendance:</strong> Jenn Gress, Ruth Cheesley, Rowan Hoskyns-Abrahall, Djamel Kherbi, Helvecio Da Silva</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Apologies:</strong> Duke Speer, Thomas Kahl</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>No-Show:</strong> Eric Lamy, Saurabh Shah, Alejandro Pascoli, Bruce Valle, Brian Ronnow, Shirat Goldstein, Michelle Bisson, Marco Richter</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting started on time</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Listings</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Working through the directory migration so no listings to process.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rowan - update on progress</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Migration and cleanup of users is pretty much done</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Ticket created when the JUG is created, back and forth to get approval, then users are created into the JUG Owners ACL and the listing is raised.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Custom fields - need to set them up, and we need to determine what they can add and what they can edit themselves</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">There will be full versioning so we can see what has changed.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Required fields will be enabled when we go live - when people log in they will have to update their listing to include their required fields before any listing will be saved</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Discussion on required fields</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Discussion on which fields need to be locked down and only changed by the JUG team (user will need to raise a ticket to open discussion)</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Name of group</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">First contact &amp; email</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Second contact &amp; email</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">URL fields</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Social media fields</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Which fields people can see</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team - internal notes, &trade; notes</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JUG Organisers - historical notes to team</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rowan will create documentation video and text which will be in the knowledgebase of the helpdesk, so that they can be live-searched when submitting a ticket.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Terms and Rules will need to be linked and accepted when they submit their first ticket (e.g. raise the request to start a JUG) at the same time as the acceptance of the requirements for creating a JUG.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Languages - currently two fields for english &amp; meeting language, but when we go fully multilingual we will need to bring those fields over to the native language. &nbsp;Ideally do this as a rolling process one language at a time.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team are to work through cleaning up the blog posts - not hugely critical but we need to tidy things up. Read less text plugin is shortening if a readmore isn&rsquo;t present.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">We will likely be able to launch the new migrated site at JAB Make it Happen.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 439, '2016-05-17 00:00:00', 439, '2016-05-17 19:45:35', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(237, 0, 68, 'Minutes of the first meeting of the SEO Team - 20th May 2016', 'minutes-of-the-fiirst-meeting-of-the-seo-team-20th', '<p>Today the SEO team had its first meeting at JAB Barcelona.</p>\r\n<p>Attendees: Ruth Cheesley, Soren Beck-Jensen,&nbsp;Andr&eacute;s Maeso Broncano</p>\r\n<p>We discussed the vision for the team being:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To support the Joomla project in ensuring that the official websites we own and manage are properly optimised</li>\r\n<li>To assist with identifying existing problems and developing strategies for addressing them</li>\r\n<li>To monitor relevant SEO metrics</li>\r\n<li>To support teams with planning new web-based projects, migrations and campaigns</li>\r\n<li>To provide guidance in SEO-related matters relevant to the Joomla CMS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>There are a lot of subdomains and sites which are currently not being actively monitored in terms of the search engine optimisation. &nbsp;As a starting point, the team will:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Identify all sites of interest (official project sites which have a public-facing presence)</li>\r\n<li>Identify what monitoring is currently in place and ensure that it is properly implemented</li>\r\n<li>Establish a set of metrics which are of interest in auditing</li>\r\n<li>Identify tools that could be used to audit the sites</li>\r\n<li>Commence audits on sites of interest</li>\r\n<li>Identify tasks which need to be completed (identified in audits)</li>\r\n<li>Build team and share tasks amongst the team members</li>\r\n<li>Communicate with team responsible for sites what issues have been identified, provide feedback and suggestions for how to improve the sites,where appropriate giving assistance in implementing</li>\r\n<li>Conduct keyword research project/s</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>It is anticipated that the team will initially be involved in identify and assisting with the resolution of problems, however in the longer-term that it will be a resource which teams can access at any stage of a project for advice, guidance and technical support. &nbsp;It is also expected that the team will be able to support the Production Leadership Team in the case of any pull requests which have an impact on SEO.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 439, '2016-05-20 00:00:00', 439, '2016-05-25 17:27:41', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(238, 41, 0, 'PLT Meeting May 1st, 2016', 'production-leadership-team-minutes-1st-may-2016', '<h3 dir="ltr">Joomla 3.5.2 status (George)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Beta on Monday (depending on health). Will tag a second beta after Manchester so all that stuff can be merged. We have already called for installation language freeze. Not this technically contains a new feature - the rebuild Joomla Update component (including a reinstall button and an upload button). We need docs for that functionality.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Because we are shipping a new feature (Joomla Update features) we need to call 3.5.2 following semver 3.6. &nbsp;George to confirm how this is going to work from marketing perspective with Mike V.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Plan:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Alpha 21st May</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Beta 25th May</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Beta 1st June</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">RC 1 - 8th June</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Stable 15th June&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The PLT agrees to rename 3.5.2 to 3.6, there will be no 3.5.2 release and we shifting numbers for the next planned releases. Chris will be the Release Leader for the next minor release &nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Joomla 3.7.x status (Chris)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Proceeding at a reasonable pace but now a bit behind schedule.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Custom fields is on track.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">New router is a bit concerning. &nbsp;I\'ve been writing the documentation for it, but I\'ve found some bugs which we need to get fixed. &nbsp;Hannes has just done a PR for one of the additional features that we want to include if possible.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Media manager - see Marco\'s item on the agenda.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Next step is to get an alpha release out. &nbsp;I\'m going to talk to George about it in Manchester next weekend. &nbsp;Possible release a week or two later depending on how well the work is proceeding.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Since the media manager is delayed anyway, I think we\'re going to be about a month behind schedule.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">I don\'t want any further "major" features in this release. &nbsp;I think we have enough for 3.6 and we need to focus now on just getting everything working.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">State of Joomla!X / UX (Marco)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">J!X See Portal report. The &ldquo;clean base&rdquo; repo got made public. Goals is still to have the CDHMS milestone to discuss merits.<br />UX. Cliff is making a lot waves and getting some interesting data in about usage, however data is skewed to not include &ldquo;already involved&rdquo; users. Data also suggest that respondees do qualify themselves as tech-savvy. Final report and follow-up queries planned to further address personas</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">State of downloads.joomla.org (Roland)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">George and Roland will arrange a meeting after JAB to get together and bring the downloads.joomla.org live. No concrete dates as of yet.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">GSoC16 (Javier)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Joomla got six slots in the programme that can be checked at:</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/organizations/5660160231997440/">https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/organizations/5660160231997440/</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Projects have just started in the present week. And students are now getting into the community, meeting the mentors and starting their projects.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Several GSOC16 repositories have been created at <a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects">https://github.com/joomla-projects</a> organization.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Budget 2016 (Robert)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Deadline for submitting the numbers were Friday last week so I requested a budget with looking at the 2015 Budget. Should be ok for us, have sent what I have requested to you all. Waiting now on response from Victor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Goals Document (Robert)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">No more work has been done on this.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">New Media Manager (Marco)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Well on its way, regrouped during JD16N, Jisse Reitsma. Reassignment of tasks, and new volunteers such as Niels Nubel. Due to personal obligations most of the work will take place / is planned for in May. <br />Asking for second low-cost &ldquo;sprint&rdquo; in &ldquo;Roompot&rdquo; solely dedicated to mediamanager.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Joomla Contributor Agreement (Viktor)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Contact OSM for update and access to the forms.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Code Sprint in Manchester (Viktor, Roland, George, Chris)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The Code Sprint will take place next week in Manchester, UK (6th - 8th May), organized by Brian Teeman. The aim is to thrash through Github issue queues to determine what is still valid, what needs a quick test, what can be closed as something we don\'t want and what can be marked for a future release (j4) etc.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Accessibility (Roland)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Now that the Routing has been merged for 3.7 I have taken on a new side project. At JDNL I was approached by someone who wants to implement accessibility into Joomla but does not know where to go. We do have an accessibility workgroup but nothing has come out of this. After contact with Pete Bui who leads this workgroup I found out he could not get coders and testers. So I have started to pull this horse forward and will be working with Pete to get this going. I have some testers and coders arranged, the GitHub repo has been created as well. Next step is for Pete to fill it with this stuff. A guy who is an expert in accessibility here in NL will work with us as well to share his knowledge and do the testing. He knows other people in the field of accessibility who are willing to test.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Stats Server (George)</h3>\r\n<p>We now have 300k rows in the database and things are starting to fall over a bit. George and Eli have been working together to improve the performance and should have something coming out next week to help deal with the issues.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 497, '2016-05-01 00:00:00', 497, '2016-05-21 21:10:20', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(239, 0, 34, 'Make it happen 2016 report of the Joomla Automated Testing Working Group', 'make-it-happen-2016-report-of-the-joomla-automated', '<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Yesterday afternoon several community members gather to participate at the Make It Happen session at JandBeyond event ( <a href="http://jandbeyond.org/programme.html?view=session&amp;id=346&amp;return=L3Byb2dyYW1tZS5odG1s">http://jandbeyond.org/programme.html?view=session&amp;id=346&amp;return=L3Byb2dyYW1tZS5odG1s</a> ).</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">The session was coordinated by Jelle Kok, Yves Hoppe and myself, Javier G&oacute;mez. The goal of the session was to help setting up the machines for testing of the new members of the team. And afterwards, the new members worked on creating their first acceptance tests for Joomla in small groups.</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">As a results more than 15 members joined the team. Members like: Allon Moritz, Juan S&aacute;nchez, Matias Aguirre, Francisco Javier Olivares, Pablo Arias, Robert Mittl, Marc Widmann, Chris Davenport , Hugh Douglas-Smith, Esteban Turcios, Philip Walton, Sigrid Gramlinger in between others.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">We had a lot of fun and the results were very productive. Here are some examples:</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;"><a href="https://twitter.com/sgramlinger/status/734117261779345409"><img src="images/reports/Screen_Shot_2016-05-22_at_13.58.12.png" alt="Screen Shot 2016 05 22 at 13.58.12" style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; widows: auto;" /></a></div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;"><a href="https://twitter.com/digitpeak/status/734117077104132100"><img src="images/reports/allon.jpg" alt="allon" /></a></div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">Around 10 pull request were created or processed in several Joomla repositories like <a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-browser">https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-browser</a>&nbsp;or <a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc16_browser-automated-tests">https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc16_browser-automated-tests</a>&nbsp;adding dozens of tests that will enhance the quality of our beloved CMS.</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="color: #222222; font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; widows: 1;">On the other side of the room we had a working group of smart developers including Yannick Gaultier, Tito Alvarez, Niels Braczek and Michael Bodnarchuk (the author of the Codeception testing framework).</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The team is working on running the tests in parallel using Docker and Continuous Integration:</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://twitter.com/JAVI_GOMEZ/status/734356104801574913"><img src="images/reports/yannick.jpg" alt="yannick" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thanks very much all for your participation and for <strong>making #Joomla happen</strong>.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 527, '2016-05-22 12:37:42', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(240, 0, 16, 'Make it Happen JaB16: Joomla! Certification Team', 'make-it-happen-jab16-joomla-certification-team', '<p>The Joomla! certification team worked on several issues during make it happen session at JandBeyond Conference 2016, Barcelona Spain. <br /><br />Team members present are;<img src="images/reports/13282174_1482308635119397_376147377_n.jpg" alt="13282174 1482308635119397 376147377 n" width="288" height="162" style="float: right;" /><br /><br />Sam Suresh (Certification Platform Team)<br />Nicolas Clavarie (Certification Platform Team)<br />Patrick Jungbluth (Certification Operation Team)<br />Luca Marzo (Certification Operation Team)<br />Anja Hage (Certification Exam Team)<br /><br />The platform team worked on Certified User Directory, PDF Certificate generation and question results role based access. We made a very good progress and all these task completed. It was a big achievement in such a short time as we are sitting next to each other and no need for an audio conference to discuss for hours. <br /><br />The operation team worked on reviewing applications for JLP. <br /><br />As at now the Certification Project is ready to launch. <br /><br />We will be running second pilot test soon.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 813, '2016-05-22 21:04:44', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(241, 0, 68, 'Minutes of the SEO Team meeting 25th May 2016', 'minutes-of-the-seo-team-meeting-25th-may-2016', '<p dir="ltr"><strong>Attendees</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Ruth Cheesley, Andr&eacute;s Maeso Broncano, Chris Wagner</p>\r\n<p><strong>Apologies</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mike Veeckmans, Elisa Foltyn, Soren Beck-Jensen</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Topics to discuss:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Sites of interest</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Ruth has compiled a list of sites that we need to focus on which have public-facing assets. &nbsp;The team will check the annotations to ensure they are all of interest, and will prioritise which need attention</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Ruth to prepare contact list for team lead of each domain to act as a point of communication<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Discussion on what metrics will be measured and what we are interested in. &nbsp;This is just a starter for ten, it will probably change as we start conducting audits and reviewing the tools we will be using.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">For audit</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Indexed pages</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Volume</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">What pages</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Errors</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Backlinks</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Per page</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Domain/s</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Anchor text</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Optimisation problems</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Robots problems</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">On page issues</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">HTML structure</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Syntax</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Etc&hellip;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Internal link structure</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Sitemaps</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Performance</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Load time</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Relevant metrics</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Analytics</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Bounce rate</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Time on site</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Pages per visit</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Relevant metrics<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Annotations!<br /><br /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Keyword research</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Develop a set of templates for providing community members with to carry out research - Ruth explained the new structure and how team members and contributors would be organised.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Establish keyword sets in different languages/countries via contributors</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Create training videos/tutorials to support contributors in helping the team conduct research<br /><br /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">For ongoing research/monitoring</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">This will mostly come out of what we find from the audit.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">May well need some custom work to implement the kind of data collection we will be needing.<br /><br /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Tools</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Sistrix - potential option to use the tool for Joomla, Chris is having a talk on Friday and will report back on our options</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Manhattan-Tool - Instant API: Nils Haack is getting back to Chris about usage of resources. Metrics / keywords would have to be found and then monitored on a daily or larger period basis.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">SEM-Tool - for keyword research. Chris to talk to Nils Haack about this.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">LinkResearchTools - Ruth to talk to Christoph Cemper about the possibility of using their Agency account.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Majestic - Andres has contacts via one of their tools and will follow up to see if we might be able to get some kind of access.<br /><br /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Problems with analytics profiles</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Discussion on subdomains loading joomla.org analytics tracking code in addition to their own</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed options of loading one profile and using cross-domain tracking versus each domain having its own tracking</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Decided it&rsquo;s not relevant to have a single profile with all oversight on subdomains (it always gets sampled, and we can query the API to get the information if needed)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Action: Request removal of the joomla.org tracking property from all hosts currently loading it, ensure they are only loading their own subdomain, ideally via GTM - Ruth to identify contacts and action.<br /><br /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Action points:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Review subdomains and set order of priority for auditing</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Touch-base with teams to ensure they know what we&rsquo;re doing</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Follow up on tools to be used &amp; test environments for auditing/crawling</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Resolve Analytics problems</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 439, '2016-05-25 17:22:33', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(242, 0, 19, 'Certification Operations Team - Meeting Notes - 26 May, 2016', 'certification-operations-team-meeting-notes-26-may', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-3bd82a2b-ed3f-181e-056f-8732f960301f" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on May 26th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Luca Marzo, Andre Dreier, Todd Woodward, Pablo Pantoja, Richard van Tilborg.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Deb Cinkus, Johan Van der Velde, Sam Suresh, Arjen Schrijvers, Hector Mansilla.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick and Luca reported news from the Make It Happen session at JandBeyond last week.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">At JaB, the Certification Platform Team had good progress: new Certified Users Directory has been created and it&rsquo;s directly connected with the Exam Platform. They worked also on the PDF Certificate.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team received important feedback from the French Community that wants to include the Joomla! Certification Exam in a complete learning project.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">The Team worked also on applications from JLPs, RCs and JUGs, many ticket have been processed.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Pablo reported that some Universities from Colombia want to create learning courses about Joomla! And their aim is to include the Certification Exam in their classes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Lawyers finally approved contracts. During the next OSM board meeting (this week), OSM will review/accept contracts, so we can start deploy them to our Joomla! Learning Partners.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay Italy asked to have an exam session on November 12, 2016. Team thinks that it could be an interesting opportunity for many people in Italy to attend the certification at a big community event.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay Austria asked to have an exam session on December 2-3, 2016. Team wants to approve the session and will help organizers to be compliant.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team noticed some trademark violations with domain names and unofficial certifications and will report them to the Joomla! Trademark &amp; Licensing Working Group in order to be processed.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team started a brainstorming document about a short agreement for JUGs/JDays that will host exam sessions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca will talk with Martijn from OSM to understand if we can use the Non-Disclosure Agreement (OSM) for Supervisors at JUGs and JoomlaDays.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Andre will ask Radek Suski (Events/JET Team) to obtain informations about the process for funding travels of Certification Team members.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick is working with Brian Mitchell (JRD Team) to list JLPs on the Joomla! Resource Directory.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Most of the applicants did not answer our email and/or tickets, so we cannot process their applications. If you applied as JLP or you asked to host a Certification Exam, please look at your mailbox and answer emails from the Certification program. If you did not received email from us, please open a support ticket at <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/support">https://certification.joomla.org/support</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 85 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2016-05-26 13:27:37', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(243, 0, 44, 'JED Team Meeting Notes - 27th May 2016', 'jed-team-meeting-notes-27th-may-2016', '<p>Today the Joomla Extensions Directory (JED) team met at 2pm GMT via Glip to discuss our progress of current tasks.</p>\r\n<p>In attendance: Matthew Baylor, Jaz Parkyn, Luca Marzo, Hugh Douglas-Smith, Rob Clayburn, Aleksander Kuczek, Anibal Sanchez</p>\r\n<p><strong>Statistics for the month of May 2016</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Extensions: 89 Published, 40 Pending Fix/Initial screening</li>\r\n<li>Tickets: 185 Processed, 61 Pending User Reply,&nbsp; 47 New</li>\r\n<li>Reviews: 635 Submitted</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Amendments to JED Extension Submission and Approval Processes</strong></p>\r\n<p>Upon submitting an extension, if it is found to have issues that need to be corrected before it can be published; developers will now have 21 days to make any necessary amendments and inform us when they have completed this via a ticket. After this time period, JED reserves the right to remove any extension that still has outstanding issues.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Faces of Code: What are your facial expressions whilst coding?</strong></p>\r\n<p>To be in with a chance to win a copy of the book &lsquo;Programming Joomla Plugins&rsquo; by Jisse Reitsma, submit a photo to social media of yourself or a friend of their facial expressions whilst writing code. Don&rsquo;t forget to use the hashtag #facesofcode</p>\r\n<p>The funniest 12 Faces of Code will receive a copy each.</p>\r\n<p>Deadline: Thursday 30th June 2016</p>\r\n<p>About the book: <a href="https://www.yireo.com/books/programming-joomla-plugins-book">https://www.yireo.com/books/programming-joomla-plugins-book</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Contributing to JED</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you find any bugs or would like to suggest an improvement, please find the issue on our JIRA Issue Tracker. Your opinion could make a significant impact on the Extensions Directory.</p>\r\n<p>To be added to our Glip developer chat, please send an email to jaz.parkyn (at) extensions.joomla.org asking for access. You will see important tasks to the right, and we will discuss general issues there. (Specific issues will be discussed within JIRA). Also, JIRA integrates with our chat system, so you can easily see new issues and replies to issues right in our chat system.</p>\r\n<p>To find out more about the JED development process and how you can contribute, please see these pages:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/contributing-code-to-the-jed">http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/contributing-code-to-the-jed</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/fun-in-jed-bug-smashing-and-feature-development">http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/fun-in-jed-bug-smashing-and-feature-development</a></li>\r\n<li><a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/how-to-collaborate-and-improve-our-jed-jab16-barcelona">http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/how-to-collaborate-and-improve-our-jed-jab16-barcelona </a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We are currently ironing out a few issues with the development environment and will provide updates on this as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p>We apologise to anyone who has already signed the JEDCA and has not yet received access to BitBucket. There was a communication issue with the sign up form, which we hope to have corrected as soon as possible. We will soon provide access to those who have already signed.</p>\r\n<p>The next JED team meeting will take place on 24th June 2016 at the same time.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 695, '2016-05-27 00:00:00', 695, '2016-06-02 07:44:16', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(244, 0, 24, 'Joomla Google Summer of Code Team Report April-May 2016', 'joomla-google-summer-of-code-team-report-april-may', '<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">GSoC Students were announced on 22nd April, 2016, Community bonding period got over on 23rd May. 24th May is the official coding period start date according to the program timelines. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-dda557b9-fd04-9f78-69ae-b99482bb78b7" style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">In past few months, following has been done in each project: </span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Scope of the project, project milestones and timelines finalized. </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Github projects have been setup and students have forked and starting doing PR&rsquo;s, basically getting familiar with Github workflow. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><ol style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We also published Github Workflow document for Mentors and Students, Thanks to Yves Hoppe for preparing this, https://docs.joomla.org/GSOC_2016_Joomla_GIT_Workflow &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: lower-roman; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We have also decided to track all project activities via Github issues, all the tasks would be assigned and tracked on Github. </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol></ol></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Students have started experimenting and researching around tools that will be used in their projects. Ex. Jasmine, Gherkin, Behat etc. </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Students have completed first JCM Articles which will contain details about the project; all posts will be published as part of next edition of JCM. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">These are all the links to all the six projects on github:</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc16_recording-action-logs" style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc16_recording-action-logs</span></a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc16_improved-multi-lingual" style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc16_improved-multi-lingual</span></a><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc16_browser-automated-tests" style="text-decoration: none;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; vertical-