	(305, 0, 13, ' 2 August, 2016 JUG Team Minutes', '2-august-2016-jug-team-minutes', '<p>In attendance:</p>\r\n<p>Djamel Kherbi<br />Jenn Gress<br />Brian Ronnow<br />Rowan Hoskyns-Abrahall</p>\r\n<p>Appologies:</p>\r\n<p>No Show:</p>\r\n<p>Alejandro Pascoli</p>\r\n<p>Helvecio da Silva</p>\r\n<p>Eric Lamy</p>\r\n<p>Saurabh Shah</p>\r\n<p>Bruce Valle</p>\r\n<p>Thomas Kahl</p>\r\n<p>Shirat Goldstein</p>\r\n<p>Michelle Bisson</p>\r\n<p>Duke Speer</p>\r\n<p>Marco Richter</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We worked with some repots of listing issues.</p>\r\n<p>Talked about moving people around to get the best our of them and the team.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 461, '2016-08-03 08:48:42', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(306, 0, 39, 'JUX Meeting August 2nd 2016', 'jux-meeting-august-2nd-2016', '<p class="p1">JUX Meeting August 2nd 2016</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Our meeting agenda can be found here:</strong><br /><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1etT48U-4kK0QwBMeaMlMEeDe6biRgxHLTbnmruUdic8/" target="_blank">https://docs.google.com/document/d/1etT48U-4kK0QwBMeaMlMEeDe6biRgxHLTbnmruUdic8/</a></p>\r\n<p class="p2"><strong>A video recording of the meeting can be found here:<br /></strong><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B6x4A5qoGgOoem5WWGtlcFpIOTg/" target="_blank">https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B6x4A5qoGgOoem5WWGtlcFpIOTg/</a></p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Meeting Recap:</strong></p>\r\n<p class="p1">The meeting was 1:15 long, the agenda was more or less covered in the first 40 minutes. The remaining time was a spirited discussion about Joomla UX and Marketing ideas and feelings. A lot of great points were made by Rich, Daniel and myself.</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Meeting Notes:</strong></p>\r\n<p class="p1">Our meeting this week was a recap of our last meeting and our strategy for August</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Points we covered:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="p1">We are putting our sprint planning on hold until the budgets get sorted</li>\r\n<li class="p1">We discussed JWC UX sessions and options</li>\r\n<li class="p1">We have a new github project repository:<br /><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/user-experience">https://github.com/joomla-projects/user-experience<br /></a>Thanks to George Wilson for setting this up. We have not done anything with it yet as it has just been set up, but we will start using it shortly and it will become a resource for discussions, tasks and work.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>August Game plan in a nutshell:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Finalize JUX Structure, Process and Strategy</li>\r\n<li class="p1">Follow up with all JUX Team applicants</li>\r\n<li class="p1">Set team roles and members for projects</li>\r\n<li class="p1">Publish 3.5 survey data</li>\r\n<li class="p1">Follow up with all 3.5 survey volunteers</li>\r\n<li class="p1">Create &amp; Release 3.6 survey / research</li>\r\n<li class="p1">Begin testing and contributing to 3.7</li>\r\n<li class="p1">Begin creating lists of most requested improvements</li>\r\n<li class="p1">Begin creating lists of resources, ideasand proposals from team members</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="p1">End of August / September, details regarding budgets and timelines should be more clear. We will re-assess the situation and our strategy as more details come in.</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Discussion Recap</strong></p>\r\n<p class="p1">I think much of our discussion, which generally related to UX and Marketing topics, express viewpoints that are shared by many in our community. The point I made is this: We all seem to know what the issues are, now it&rsquo;s up to us to create solutions. Listening to our users and creating new solutions for them is the purpose of our team. The UX team can provide new direction and leadership in many ways within our community. This requires change, and change is not always easy. Not everyone will agree with our thoughts or approach, but we are here to find solutions. We can change the situation for the better through our work.</p>\r\n<p class="p1">Our next meeting is in two weeks, exact time is TDB and will be scheduled through a doodle poll in the JUX working group Glip chat room.</p>\r\n<p class="p1"><strong>Cliff Pfeifer</strong><br />JUX Team Lead</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 673, '2016-08-03 00:00:00', 673, '2016-08-03 23:48:06', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(307, 0, 19, 'Certification Operations Team - Meeting Notes - August 04, 2016', 'certification-operations-team-meeting-notes-august', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-3c902151-55a8-07f6-b617-a8b3f525f541" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on August, 4th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Andre Dreier, Arjen Schrijvers, Pablo Pantoja.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Deb Cinkus, Johan Van der Velde, Sam Suresh, Patrick Jungbluth, Richard van Tilborg, Hector Mansilla, Todd Woodward.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca reported news from Steering Meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Certification Team completed successfully the second Pilot Test. The Joomla! Exam Platform works well. Platform Team will work to improve the Certified Users Directory.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team onboarded a Developer as new member and he will work on the Certified Users Directory.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team reviewed a couple of questions to improve the quality of the test.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Operations Team provided OSM contracts for JUGs and JoomlaDays organizers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Contracts should be approved by OSM&rsquo;s Board of Directors.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca refactored both application forms for JUGs and JoomlaDays and asked Richard to change the website in order to publish new forms.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">The &ldquo;Host Exams&rdquo; page on Certification Website will be improved.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca developed also new forms for screen and process applications as JUGs and JoomlaDays, to improve efficiency of the evaluation processes within COT.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Next steps: RC application form will be refactored and a new form to screen such kind of applications will be developed.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">If contracts will be ready, we plan to approve an exam session at JoomlaDay Malaysia on mid-August.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">All pending/incomplete applications as Joomla! Learning Partner will be rejected next days and people will be invited to re-submit the application using the new form.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p>Meeting ends after 60 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2016-08-04 13:05:55', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(308, 0, 7, 'Joomla! 3.6 Marketing & Landing Page Debriefing', 'joomla-36-marketing-a-landing-page-debrieifing', '<p>Meeting notes can be found here : <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/19sp207EN6lRQntndj36k4jev-1GX-aiGMyrqt3WqlqM/edit">https://docs.google.com/document/d/19sp207EN6lRQntndj36k4jev-1GX-aiGMyrqt3WqlqM/edit</a></p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 485, '2016-08-05 00:00:00', 485, '2016-08-05 18:21:41', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
