	(385, 0, 19, 'COT - Meeting notes - December 1, 2016', 'cot-meeting-notes-december-1-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-660cfa1b-ba98-fc57-9c28-af30fdfa11ef" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on December 1st, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Patrick Jungbluth, Oscar Ortiz, Todd Woodward</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Johan Van der Velde, Andre Dreier, Pablo Pantoja, Richard van Tilborg, Arjen Schrijvers.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Oscar is screening and evaluating Regional Coordinators applications.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Oscar has been elected Assistant Team Leader of Certification Operations Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Todd has been assigned as Supervisor for the exam session at JoomlaDay Florida 2017.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed the &ldquo;strategy letter&rdquo; sent to the whole JCP Team by Luca early this week.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team planned the first meeting with all the Regional Coordinators for December 12, 2016.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Certification Team is working on a mid-term Plan, defining goals and strategy for the next year.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Community events:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay Austria with Wilco Alsemgeest as Supervisor (December 2, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 35 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 72, 1, 669, '2016-12-01 13:35:30', 0, '2016-12-01 13:36:07', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(386, 0, 39, 'JUX Meeting November 30th 2016', 'jux-meeting-november-30th-2016', '<h2>JUX Meeting November 30th 2016</h2>\r\n<p>Wednesday November 30nd 17:00 UTC Time Duration 1:00</p>\r\n<p><strong>Participants:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dawn Russell</li>\r\n<li>Rishi Vishwakarma</li>\r\n<li>Rich Starkie</li>\r\n<li>Niels Braczek</li>\r\n<li>Crystal Harris</li>\r\n<li>Cliff Pfeifer</li>\r\n<li>Charlie Lodder</li>\r\n<li>Brian Peat</li>\r\n<li>Armands Vijups</li>\r\n<li>Allon Moritz</li>\r\n<li>Elisa Foltyn</li>\r\n<li>Britta Stender</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Agenda Items &amp; Minutes:</h2>\r\n<h3><strong>Team Business</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Team Meeting Time Poll:&nbsp;<br />Please choose your best times for a WEEKLY meeting for the entire month of December<br /><a href="http://doodle.com/poll/w2mnm8wwvv8cb8mc">http://doodle.com/poll/w2mnm8wwvv8cb8mc</a></li>\r\n<li>Everyone must complete the Team Member details form to be eligible for Team Member or Team Contributor status:&nbsp;<a href="https://goo.gl/forms/TwoC3UNBvkQ7Mt322">https://goo.gl/forms/TwoC3UNBvkQ7Mt322</a>&nbsp;If your contact information has changed or does change at any point in time, please fill it out again.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>Transition and team structure updates:</strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong>JUX Leadership</strong></p>\r\n<p>Team Leader position still pending Transition team ruling on election results. At this point in time, it is more of a formality than anything else and we are moving forward under the assumption that Cliff Pfeifer will remain as team lead. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cliff Pfeifer names Dawn Russell and Britta Stender as Assistant Team Leads. Both have shown exemplary attitudes, exceptional organizational and communcation skills, and both embrace the spirit of collaboration and the overall vision of the JUX team. The transistion structure only includes one assistant lead position, should a time come where we need to choose only one it will be addressed by our team at that time.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Accessibility Team</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Deemed to remain as a UX sub team until the transistion is complete.</li>\r\n<li>Lead Crystal Harris</li>\r\n<li>Team will be focused on mostly technical aspects to make it conform to government standards.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Sub-Team Leader of the UX Team - she will have the freedom to make the decisions with relation to implementing accessibility.</li>\r\n<li>After establishing the active volunteers, go through Joomla 3.x and Joomla 4x and the websites to ascertain where we stand on Accessibility. Will be able to see where we are falling short and where we need to work. <br />Statement on the website is very out of date.</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Focus on strategy first.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>T<strong>eam applications, guidelines &amp; onboarding</strong></p>\r\n<p>Currently have 70 pending applications. Hold off on adding anyone new into the team at this point while we are in planning mode. Once we have the plan established then we can integrate them into the subteams or projects.<br /><br />There are a number of pending applicants for the JUX team who will be followed up with once our team structure and strategy is more solid. New contributors need immediate task assignments otherwise they lose interest quickly<br /><br /></p>\r\n<h3>Team strategy and planning (Britta and Dawn)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Mission: UX team provides support and guidance in two main areas of the Joomla! Project:</li>\r\n<li>Joomla CMS Releases (Share Idea for creating the Project Charters)</li>\r\n<li>Joomla 3.7 (Custom Fields Testing and Implementation) - Elisa - urgently need feedback from people on custom fields.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Joomla 3.8 (Media Manager)</li>\r\n<li>Joomla 4</li>\r\n<li>Joomla.org Website(s) (Testing, Refinement, Reporting)</li>\r\n<li>Process for Implementation (Gain Approval, Collaborate with other teams)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Initial sketch of how UX Project Organization will be structured&nbsp;illustrating how collaboration across teams would happen.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Notes from meeting: </strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will release a strategy for moving forward to describe how we can collaborate across teams to implement a new feature change, using Joomla 3.7 as a starting point. The goal is to streamline communication and to open new lines of communication. Helping people work together to achieve goals. Also responsible for testing, research, and making recommendations. We will present the project charter next week for Joomla 3.7. This diagram is not recommending a structure change - rather we are proposing a UX Project Organization chart that illustrates how people across teams will collaborate and gain approval on projects and features that touch different teams (ie: marketing, production, UX, documentation, translations).&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>We&rsquo;ll really have an impact with testing phase. (Crystal) - testing for bugs different from testing for user experience - while testing for bugs can discover UX issues it is not as accurate - it can be done with quick screenshots and wireframes - asking them to complete a series of tests and see how they do it. Better when research done in advance. Crystal could provide advisory capacity with regards to user experience testing.</li>\r\n<li>Rich - can the UX team nix a new feature request? UX can provide data backed up with research to recommend or vote down a feature. Possible to offer a liaison between PLT and UX when new features are being discussed. Britta - we can suggest that having UX involved will facilitate the success of the project &nbsp;- Rich &ldquo;UX is driving the user experience for Joomla.&rdquo; Cliff - we don&rsquo;t have the authority to stop a team from implementing a new feature. Hopefully our team becomes a resource for other teams and creating an environment to ensure the success of the project.</li>\r\n<li>Crystal - &nbsp;I think the biggest challenge this team faces (and this speaks to your question maybe) is creating a UX-first culture in the project - where it\'s not an afterthought but the first thing people consider. That\'s a HUGE challenge and I think one of the things that should be in our goal is educating the joomla volunteer community about the importance and scope of UX. If there\'s a UX-first culture or user-first culture then it\'s a lot easier to convince people based on research vs based on who shouts louder.</li>\r\n<li>Joomla! 3.8 - Update on Media Manager Sprint in Vienna - (Elisa)&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Visual Architecture, UI and Implementation</li>\r\n<li>Elisa - How to visualize the image text so the user experience is good?</li>\r\n<li>Elisa - New media manager will have ACL.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Elisa - facilitate the process by coordinating with Britta and Dawn to get the project charter complete.</li>\r\n<li>Allon - has a repo - put together a list of questions.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>https://github.com/joomla-projects/media-manager-improvement</li>\r\n<li>Some of the spec is written down here: https://github.com/joomla-projects/media-manager-improvement/wiki</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Research &amp; Testing&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>Cliff - working to organize all of the data that we have and make it public. Working with David Stetson and Eric to get the data together.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Research status update</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will create a Glip channel for JUX Research Team</li>\r\n<li>Research Team will coordinate their own meetings as necessary</li>\r\n<li>Preparation and Publishing of existing results</li>\r\n<li>2016 data is mostly processed</li>\r\n<li>Raw feedback is mostly sorted</li>\r\n<li>Individual project and platform recommendations in progress</li>\r\n<li>Full 2016 research report is in progress</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Research needs assistance with:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Analysis and recommendations from research findings<br />If you have ideas or conclusions, write them out and add them</li>\r\n<li>Finding related issues and PR&rsquo;s on Github<br />Some recommended changes are already in progress, find them to streamline development</li>\r\n<li>Matching raw feedback with personas<br />We have existing personas that can be used, or new personas can be created. If you have better or new ideas, we want to see them</li>\r\n<li>Creating the next survey / research effort</li>\r\n<li>User Testing process for:<br />J4 backend, 3.7 release, Custom Fields and Media Manager</li>\r\n<li>Follow up with previous survey participants<br />We have more than 500 volunteers for future research</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Sprint Planning</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>UX Sprint January 20-23 2017 - Did not discuss in meeting, will discuss with Sprint Attendees outside of regular team meetings</li>\r\n<li>Create a glip channel for Sprint Attendees</li>\r\n<li>Begin planning high level sprint agenda and goals</li>\r\n<li>December / January JUX Team Roadmap leading up to the sprint</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 1, 73, 1, 673, '2016-12-01 15:58:49', 0, '2016-12-01 16:20:59', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(387, 0, 44, 'JED Team Meeting - December 02, 2016', 'jed-team-meeting-december-02-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-d87b8f7b-c062-7e5c-067b-39bbe0470f4b" dir="ltr">Today the Joomla! Extensions Directory (JED) team met at 2pm GMT via Glip to discuss our progress of current tasks.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Matthew Baylor, Jaz Parkyn, Luca Marzo, Anibal Sanchez, Hugh Douglas-Smith</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Statistics for the month of November 2016</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Extensions: 159 submitted, 93 processed, 51 pending fix</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Tickets: 224 submitted, 137 processed</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Reviews: 516 submitted</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Jaz Parkyn has been elected Team Leader of the Joomla! Extensions Directory Team.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Anibal Sanchez has been selected as Assistant Team Leader for the JED Team.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team wants to tribute a huge &ldquo;Thank you!&rdquo; to Matthew Baylor for his long service as JED Team Leader.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Last week Jaz, Anibal and other members arranged a &ldquo;Ticket Sprint&rdquo; to drain the ticket system queue.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed about issues with fake reviews and a way to ensure a quick review evaluation and approval. Hugh is working on a new algorithm to easily detect and unpublish fake / spam reviews.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed also a series of Improvements needed by the Review Management UI, in order to have a faster workflow.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Updates to Listing Requirements</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">A reminder that all extensions listed on the JED will soon be required to use the Joomla Update System. This will help to ensure that site owners are always notified of when a new version of their installed extensions is available. Keeping extensions up to date can help to improve security.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">This change is a mandatory requirement and checks will be added to the JED Checker. The error code will be: US1 - update sites not present in xml file. This new requirement will come into force on January 10th 2017.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">** With regards to extensions already listed on JED, they will not be unpublished if they are not in compliance with this new requirement. Instead a popup warning will be shown to users when clicking the Download button, informing them that the extension doesn\'t support update servers and therefore must be updated manually. **</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Further information can be found in the minutes from 1st July 2016.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The JED knowledgebase article covering update server implementation is available from the below link.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/joomla-update-system-requirement">http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/joomla-update-system-requirement</a></p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Contributing to JED</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you find any bugs or would like to suggest an improvement, please find the issue on our JIRA Issue Tracker. Your opinion could make a significant impact on the Extensions Directory.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">To be added to our Glip developer chat, please send an email to jaz.parkyn (at) extensions.joomla.org asking for access. You will see important tasks to the right, and we will discuss general issues there. (Specific issues will be discussed within JIRA). Also, JIRA integrates with our chat system, so you can easily see new issues and replies to issues right in our chat system.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">To find out more about the JED development process and how you can contribute, please see these pages:</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">-<a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/contributing-code-to-the-jed"> http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/contributing-code-to-the-jed</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">-<a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/fun-in-jed-bug-smashing-and-feature-development"> http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/fun-in-jed-bug-smashing-and-feature-development</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">-<a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/how-to-collaborate-and-improve-our-jed-jab16-barcelona"> http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/how-to-collaborate-and-improve-our-jed-jab16-barcelona</a></p>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>', NULL, 1, 74, 1, 669, '2016-12-02 16:33:58', 0, '2016-12-02 16:34:46', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(388, 0, 78, 'Certification Steering Meeting - December 06, 2016', 'certification-steering-meeting-december-06-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-ea8c2050-d49e-914a-4fa1-37f39a90ac05" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Steering Group meets every Tuesday at 2:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on December 06, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Sam Suresh, Patrick Jungbluth, Stefanie Thielman, Richard van Tilborg, Sarah Watz, Michael Snoeren, Oscar Ortiz.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Arjen Schrijvers.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Oscar Ortiz joined the Steering meeting as new Assistant Team Leader for Certification Operations Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team is working on the categorisation system to prepare it for the new maintenance system.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Certification Team wants to underline that the Joomla! Certification is a personal achievement and not a company one.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Johan Van der Velde resigned from his position as ATL for Certification Marketing Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Certification Marketing Team is working on a Marketing Plan for 2017.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Certification Team wants to underline that Joomla! Learning Partners cannot profit selling exams. Exams must be sold at the official price. Profit and additional fees can be applied to training services (lessons, workshop, training materials, courses).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team and Platform Team are working on a &ldquo;Congratulation&rdquo; email for people who pass the exam.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team is working on the new version of the Certified Users Directory.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team created automatic certificates for JLPs and Certified Users that will be available through the Exam Platform.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed feedbacks coming from latest sessions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>Meeting ends after 50 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 75, 1, 669, '2016-12-06 14:51:34', 0, '2016-12-06 14:52:11', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(389, 0, 13, '6th of December  2016 User Groups Team (JUG) meeting report', '8th-of-december-2016-user-groups-team-jug-meeting', '<p dir="ltr">In attendance:</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Jenn Gress</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rowan Hoskyns-Abrahall</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Brian Row</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Djamel Kherbi</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Apologies:</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Eric Lamy</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Duke Speer</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">No Shows:</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Bruce Valle</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marco Richter</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We had our bi-monthly meeting first meeting for the month of December, helded &nbsp;from 19 pm to 20 pm CET on Google hangout, the following items were discussed.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Listings updates, several new JUGS as been approved the last two weeks, we have new JUG in Burkina Fasso and Italy, Jenn is working on listing from Minsk (Russia) and Breizh (France). Brian is working on updates and processing a new Listing from Madrid (Spain), Djamel is Following up with listings from Casamassima (Italy) and updating some listings.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rowan is working on our monthly newsletter for the Joomla user group with the JUG activity who happened around the world, to maintain informed all the JUG organizers around the world.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">We are working on the User Group Team budget draft for 2017/ 2018.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The next meeting will be on the held on the 20th of December, Djamel will Lead the meeting and Brian Row will take minutes.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>', NULL, 1, 76, 3, 468, '2016-12-07 04:20:01', 468, '2016-12-07 15:09:27', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(390, 0, 16, 'Certification Platform Team Report 7 December 2016', 'certification-platform-team-report-7-december-2016', '<p>Attendees: Sam Suresh, Michael Snoeren, Oscar Ortiz, Chris Keen<br /><br />Meeting notes published to the community:<br /><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sam reported news from steering meeting.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; New enhancements on picking users directly from db is require parent ID in the user params. Michael to work on this. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sam created a view for JLPs to view their students and grades. This will be available once parent ID is added to user params. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; All dashboards require CSS or look and feel improvement. Oscar to work on this. Also new dashboard for Supervisors to be created. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The development site to be isolated from production server. Chris to check with exam team for downtime. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; User and JLP printable PDF certificates will be available on user dashboard this week onwards. <br /><br />The platform team members meet every Wednesday 7pm GMT+8.</p>', NULL, 1, 77, 1, 813, '2016-12-07 11:32:03', 0, '2016-12-07 11:37:34', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(391, 0, 25, 'JBS after the Transition', 'jbs-after-the-transition', '<p>Last month, as a step towards the new structure, a new team leadership for the Joomla! Bug Squad was elected.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="joomlers/270-niels-braczek">Niels Braczek</a>&nbsp;Team Lead</li>\r\n<li><a href="joomlers/1054-demis-palma">Demis Palma</a>&nbsp;Assistant Lead</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The Bug Squad has not been very active lately as a group, although many of its members have worked on tracker items together with other contributors (thank you for that).</p>\r\n<p>This is going to change. According to the new structure, the JBS has members and contributors. Because of that, two different Glip channels were implemented - one open for everybody (the orginal JBS channel, \'Bug Squad Public Discussion\'), and one for team members only (\'Bug Squad Team\'). The members will meet on that channel once a month and publish the meeting notes on the Volunteers Portal.</p>\r\n<p>Since membership comes with privileges, it will not be granted without qualifying for it. Usually, a new member starts as a contributor, providing or testing fixes on the tracker. Nobody needs to be a member of the JBS to do that. After some time, that person might want to request membership (or even be asked to join), and will be accepted depending on the contributions.</p>\r\n<p>After a certain period of inactivity - currently three months -, people will be removed from the members list.</p>\r\n<p>For the moment, the Skype channel will stay open for fast communication between people working together on issues. Nevertheless, the only official channel is the public Glip channel. Sub teams may choose realtime communications like Skype or Hangouts that suits them most.</p>\r\n<p>We are just starting to get everything on track again. Consolidating communication channels and defining requirements for membership is only a beginning. Discussions will be held with other working groups about responsibilities and cooperation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Niels Braczek</p>\r\n<p>Team Lead</p>\r\n<p>BTW: Why not head over to the tracker and just test a PR?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 78, 3, 625, '2016-12-07 22:29:34', 625, '2016-12-07 22:36:24', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(392, 41, 0, 'PLT Meeting - November 30, 2016', 'plt-meeting-november-30-2016', '<h3 id="docs-internal-guid-6e1aa8cc-dc30-560b-9aea-5d767d5eb81d" dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Presents</strong>: Javier, Luca, Robert, Tessa, Roland, Chris</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Absents</strong>: Marco, George, Viktor</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Time</strong>: &nbsp;16:00 CET</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Total time of the meeting</strong>: &nbsp;150 minutes</p>\r\n<p><strong>Note</strong><em>: this meeting report has been published late in order to allow absent members to read and review it.</em></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Previous meeting minutes</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="leadership/production-leadership-team/reports/353-plt-meeting-october-20-2016">https://volunteers.joomla.org/leadership/production-leadership-team/reports/353-plt-meeting-october-20-2016</a></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Transition Process</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The Joomla! Transition Team started the transition process, driving the Joomla! Community to the new model and structure. All the teams arranged call for nominations and elections to elect Team Leaders and Assistant Team Leaders. PLT (as CLT and OSM) will be dissolved at the end of the Transition and will be replaced by the Production Department. All teams currently under the PLT responsibility will fall under the new Production Department.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Accessibility Team</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">This team has been moved as subteam of the User Experience (UX) Team after a PLT vote.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Automated Testing Working Group</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Yves Hoppe has been elected Team Leader. Javier Gomez will serve as Assistant Team Leader. Team cleaned up the volunteers list on the JVP and moved inactive people to the Honour Roll.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Bug Squad</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Niels Braczek has been elected Team Leader. Demis Palma will serve as Assistant Team Leader.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">CMS Maintenance Team</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca will arrange a call for nomination to elect a Team Leader and then an Assistant for this team.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">CMS Release Team</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">PLT will get in touch with this team and will arrange a call for nomination to elect a Team Leader and then an Assistant for this team.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Core Translation Team</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Ilagnayeru (MIG) Manickam has been confirmed as Team Leader. This team will continue working as a &ldquo;Translation Coordination Team&rdquo;, helping localisation teams to translate the CMS and create language packs.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Documentation Team</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Sandra Thevenet has been elected as Team Leader. Assistant and additional roles will be filled as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">en-GB User Interface Text Working Group</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Brian Teeman is the Team Leader. Assistant will be announced soon.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Framework Team</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">George Wilson will serve as Team Leader. Assistant and additional roles will be filled as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Joomla! X Working Group</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marco Dings will serve as Team Leader. Assistant is Niels Braczec</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Security Strike Team (JSST)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">After the resignation of Viktor, Michael Babker took the lead of the team. Assistant and additional roles will be filled as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">SQL Optimization Working Group</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Javier will get in touch with this Team in order to get further information about the progress of the election process.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">User Experience (UX) Team</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Cliff Pfeifer will lead the UX Team. Further discussions came up about the team structure and about the creation of some subteams. A Design Team will be created as subteam of the UX Team as soon as the transition will be completed.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Web Services Team</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Chris will get in touch with this Team in order to get further information about the progress of the election process. This team is in a standby phase, because some changes to the core are needed before to add the Web Services layer that has been already designed.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion outline</h3>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Budget update (Robert)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">For 2016, as of November 30, we are at 65% of budget expenses.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Google Summer of Code Projects (Javier, Roland)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">PLT voted and approved merging of the following GSoC projects:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Improving menu item workflow in Joomla!</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Shareable drafted content</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Improved Multilingual</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Roland is following the Shareable Drafted Content PR and he&rsquo;s working to fix the &ldquo;itemid&rdquo; issue in order to show a &ldquo;real-life&rdquo; appearance of the content, including the modules and other stuff, multilingual issues have been fixed.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Joomla! 3.7 (George)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">CMS Release Team published a roadmap for Joomla! 3.7 that is also the staging branch of the CMS now on Github. 3.7 Roadmap is available at: <a href="https://www.joomla.org/announcements/release-news/5692-road-to-joomla-3-7.html">https://www.joomla.org/announcements/release-news/5692-road-to-joomla-3-7.html</a></p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Reports from Automated Testing (Javier)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The team has been focused on preparing the code sprint that will take place in Munich between the 9th and the 11th of december 2016. The results will be published in the Joomla! Magazine.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">&ldquo;No code attached&rdquo; reports (Roland)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The issue tracker has a bulk of issues that has no code attached. In the future, Bug Squad Team should do something about that. Either close them or do a code sprint or something to get them resolved.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">CREDITS file out of date (Luca)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">As previously announced, PLT removed out of date content from the CREDITS file and moved all the contributors list to a dedicated page in the Joomla! Documentation.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/12534">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/12534</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://docs.joomla.org/Joomla:Joomla_Version_Credits">https://docs.joomla.org/Joomla:Joomla_Version_Credits</a></p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Pizza Bugs and Fun NL (Roland)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">25 people attended the event in the Netherlands and pushed a lot of tests and comments to existing PRs and issues on the tracker. Due to the success of the initiative, Roland will organize several PBFs in the Netherlands next year.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Out of date Language Packs (Luca)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Core Translation Team started moving packages to Crowdin and Roland is working with Thomas Hunziker to move sync scripts to a Project&rsquo;s server.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Weblinks component (Chris)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Weblinks 3.6.0-beta has been released. &nbsp;Another beta or RC will follow soon.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Votes Summary</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">During this month, PLT had the following votes:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Appoint Marco Dings as PLT Representative to Code of Conduct Team (Passed)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Media Manager Sprint 27 november 2015 in Vienna (Passed)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Move Accessibility Team as subteam of UX Team (Passed)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Improving menu item workflow in Joomla! GSOC (Passed)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL, 1, 79, 1, 669, '2016-12-08 02:07:36', 0, '2016-12-08 02:10:09', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(393, 3, 0, 'CLT Meeting Notes November 17, 2016', 'clt-meeting-notes-november-17-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-f98cf006-df79-4a2c-eb51-80a436550ed6" dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Meeting Notes CLT - November 17, 2016</span></p>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Participants:</span><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"> </span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Mike Veeckmans</span><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"><br class="kix-line-break" /></span><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Sandra Thevenet</span><span style="fon