 underline !important;">https://github.com/joomla-projects/joomla-systemtest-env</a><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;">Tito and Javier will try to run Dockers on Travis and see if Parallel testing is possible on travis, this would be a huge step forward for the group.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><a href="http://blog.travis-ci.com/2015-08-19-using-docker-on-travis-ci/" target="_blank" style="cursor: pointer; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #1155cc !important; text-decoration: underline !important;">http://blog.travis-ci.com/2015-08-19-using-docker-...</a><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /></p>\r\n<h3 style="font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; line-height: normal; margin-top: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3 style="font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; line-height: normal; margin-top: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">## Codeception tests for Webservices (Javier)</h3>\r\n<p><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;">A proposal for testing the Webservices API was sent through this:&nbsp;</span><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/webservices/pull/22#issuecomment-137412663" target="_blank" style="cursor: pointer; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #1155cc !important; text-decoration: underline !important;">https://github.com/joomla-projects/webservices/pul...</a><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;"></span><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/webservices/pull/17" target="_blank" style="cursor: pointer; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #1155cc !important; text-decoration: underline !important;"><br /><br /></a></p>\r\n<h3 style="font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; line-height: normal; margin-top: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">## Documentation (Javier, Kshitij and Valerie)</h3>\r\n<p><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;">No updates. Work in progress:&nbsp;</span><a href="https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception" target="_blank" style="cursor: pointer; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #1155cc !important; text-decoration: underline !important;">https://docs.joomla.org/Testing_Joomla_Extensions_with_Codeception</a><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;">.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;">Team has decided to create a common steps/guidelines for setting up Codeception tests, following the way we currently do&nbsp;for the tests in com_weblinks. All the documentation needs to be in Sync.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;">This will be added as one of the Goal during the Testing Sprint.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /></p>\r\n<h3 style="font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; line-height: normal; margin-top: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">## Easy tool to run the tests(Daniel,&nbsp;Yves)</h3>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;">We need help with windows machines. If you have time to volunteer please ping Javier in Glip</span><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;">Daniel dimitrov, and Yves will help on this&nbsp;</span><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /></p>\r\n<h3 style="font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; line-height: normal; margin-top: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3 style="font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; color: #000000; line-height: normal; margin-top: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; background-image: none; background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: initial;">## Next meeting is planned to happen on</h3>\r\n<p><span style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;">14th Oct, 2015:&nbsp;</span><br style="color: #000000; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal;" /><a href="http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.html?msg=15th+Meeting+for+the+Automation+Working+Group&amp;iso=20151014T2030&amp;p1=438&amp;ah=1" target="_blank" style="cursor: pointer; font-family: proxima-nova, \'Helvetica Neue\', HelvetitcaNeue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #1155cc !important; text-decoration: underline !important;">http://www.timeanddate.com/worldclock/fixedtime.ht...</a></p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 525, '2015-09-23 00:00:00', 525, '2015-09-23 18:07:16', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Joomla Contributor Agreement (Viktor)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Viktor contacted Mark Dexter and Marijke Stuijvenberg but received no access. Now Viktor will contact Martijn Boomsma to get access to the JCA and proceed from there. One change needs to be made to the JCA. The AGPL must be removed from the JCA.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Accessibility (Roland)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Joomla has an accessibility statement: <a href="https://www.joomla.org/accessibility-statement.html">https://www.joomla.org/accessibility-statement.html</a> The goal is to make Joomla meet an agreed accessibility standard. At first the standard needs to be decided upon.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Review UX Document from Cliff (George)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The PLT has no objections to the draft UX document put forward by Cliff Pfeiffer looking at the results of the UX survey. George will work with Cliff to start formulating concrete proposals for the issues raised.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Decoupling (Chris)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We still are committed to our decoupling program.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">However the PLT still feel there are issues in terms of releasing and the logistics of maintaining and releasing components.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">There has also been a problem with keeping track of open PR&rsquo;s in the weblinks github - if we decouple most core components then we also will have a maintainability issue. As a result Chris D. is going to take charge of maintaining <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/weblinks">Weblinks</a>.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Furthermore we feel that shipping core as empty would be a turnoff for people new to Joomla so the logistics of bundling some components when building the CMS (that could be uninstalled) is also something that needs investigating.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Releasing New Version of Install From Web (Robert)</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Robert suggests that we use a small framework to setup an API to feed the Install from Web to improve performance.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Joomla 5 Year Plan</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">After a request from Mike V on Day 1 the PLT spent the last part of Day 2 assembling a 5 year plan for the project. This is still in an ideas form so will not be published at this stage but will be further worked on over the coming months both internally and in coordination with the marketing team</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 497, '2016-05-30 00:00:00', 497, '2016-05-30 22:43:02', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(246, 0, 19, 'Certification Operations Team - Meeting Notes - 2 June, 2016', 'certification-operations-team-meeting-notes-2-june', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-9a527905-1129-dd3d-7dae-493e0b991897" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on June 2nd, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Luca Marzo, Andre Dreier, Pablo Pantoja, Richard van Tilborg, Arjen Schrijvers.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Deb Cinkus, Todd Woodward, Johan Van der Velde, Sam Suresh, Hector Mansilla.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Andre shared informations received from Radek and Rowan, respectively from Joomla! Events Team and Joomla! Event Travellers Program.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will draft a process for travel refund for team members into next weeks.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick reported news from the Steering Meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca reported that starting June, 6 2016, PayPal won\'t be available anymore in Turkey due to recent laws about payment infrastructure. So Exam Platform won&rsquo;t be able to accept PayPal payments in Turkey. Currently Team is investigating on other ways to handle payments for JLPs and exam candidates in Turkey.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">OSM board will approve Contracts within a week.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Richard showed Team badges for Joomla! Learning Partners coming from Elisa (Marketing Working Group).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca is keeping up to date a complete list of members of the Certification Working groups members and ensuring that all of them sign the Non-Disclosure Agreement.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca suggested to adopt a policy about &ldquo;inactive volunteers&rdquo;, since team doesn&rsquo;t need badge holder people. Arjen suggested to send notification email to inactive members, if they don&rsquo;t answer within a week, they will be removed from the Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will start involving new members as &ldquo;Contributors&rdquo; as described in the new model/structure document. This will ensure the compatibility when the Transition process will take place.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">To ensure a quality exam, team thinks that 1 supervisor per 20/25 people should be ok.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick and Luca are working on a huge review of the application/qualification process for JLPs, JUGs and JDays, in order to reduce the workload of the Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Most of the applicants did not answer our email and/or tickets, so we cannot process their applications. If you applied as JLP or you asked to host a Certification Exam, please look at your mailbox and answer emails from the Certification program. If you did not received email from us, please open a support ticket at <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/support">https://certification.joomla.org/support</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 50 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 0, 0, 669, '2016-06-02 12:50:37', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(247, 0, 45, 'Catchup Report', 'catchup-report', '<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The capital team, although have been working, has failed to post timely reports. This report will serve on catch up since our last report. We apologize for this oversight. We have been having bi-weekly meetings regularly since JWC.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 14.666666666666666px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We also will commit to posting a report within one week of our standing meetings on these remaining dates in 2016:</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 15.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Tuesday, June 14, 2016</span><span style="font-size: 15.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br class="kix-line-break" /></span><span style="font-size: 15.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; bac