	(342, 0, 19, 'COT - Meeting notes - October 6, 2016', 'cot-meeting-notes-october-6-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-473e76c0-99fc-da0e-9297-b3927eb530a6" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on October 6th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Patrick Jungbluth, Arjen Schrijvers, Oscar Ortiz.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Johan Van der Velde, Todd Woodward, Andre Dreier, Richard van Tilborg, Pablo Pantoja.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick reported news from the last Steering meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">COT will send to the approved JLPs the Welcome Pack during this week.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay Italy applied again for a session and it has been approved.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Steering Meeting reviewed the experience of the JLP certification session held at JoomlaDay Denver (USA), supervised by Sarah Watz. She provided a very detailed feedback.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca talked about the Certification Program at Joomla! Festival in Italy last week and he received a lot of positive feedbacks.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team sent a welcome newsletter to approved JLPs yesterday.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team is reviewing questions to improve quality and consistency.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Certification Program has now 19 approved Joomla! Learning Partners, coming from Italy, Austria, France, Malaysia, Norway, Croatia, Netherlands, Nigeria, Spain, Botswana, Germany.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">COT received and approved the application to host an exam session at JoomlaDay Austria on early december.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Andre decided to step down from the ATL position and to take a pause from the Certification Program.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at <strong>Community events</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Joomla! World Conference</strong> (Canada) with Sarah Watz as Supervisor (<strong>November 11</strong>, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>JoomlaDay Italy</strong> with Luca Marzo as Supervisor (<strong>November 12</strong>, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>JoomlaDay Austria</strong> with Stefanie Thielmann as Supervisor (<strong>December 2</strong>, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming Exam sessions at <strong>Joomla! Learning Partners</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Colt Engine in Pisa, Italy on <strong>October 15</strong>, 2016.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 35 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 29, 1, 669, '2016-10-06 12:33:43', 0, '2016-10-06 12:35:08', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(343, 0, 17, 'Certification Marketing Team - Meeting Notes October 3, 2016', 'certification-marketing-team-meeting-notes-october', '<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Joomla! Certification Marketing Team (MT) meets every 2 weeks on monday at 20:00 PM CET. This meeting was held on October, 3rd, 2016 on Glip.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 16pt; margin-bottom: 4pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Team members</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance:</span> <span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;Richard van Tilborg, Andr&aacute;s R&aacute;tonyi, Andrea Gentil</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents:</span><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> &nbsp;Mike Veeckmans, Johan van der Velde, Elisa Foltyn, Robert Wilson, Sarah Watz, Rogelio Alvarado, Eric Lamy, Adamzy Lee, </span></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 16pt; margin-bottom: 4pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Discussion Outline</span></h3>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The newsletter for JUGs is ready. </span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We gonna create the following groups into AcyMailing, then we can import the email addresses into the appropriate group:</span></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: circle; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JLP</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: circle; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JUGS</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: circle; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">JoomlaDays</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: circle; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Voted people badge.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We talked about the Steering Group meeting on tuesday and its result.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">We tried to find a time to work on the website simultaneously with several persons.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Next meeting will be on: 17 october 2016 - from 20.00 to 21.25 our CET.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-fa7bb3ba-9abc-f5a8-3630-71527605711c" style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 13.3333px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Meeting ends after 25 minutes.</span></p>', NULL, 1, 30, 2, 1202, '2016-10-06 16:01:37', 1202, '2016-10-06 16:05:24', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(344, 0, 78, 'Certification Steering Meeting - October 11, 2016', 'certification-steering-meeting-october-11-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-31df8c9e-b40c-7cd1-2e0f-94299785a3d6" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Steering Group meets every Tuesday at 2:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on October 11th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Patrick Jungbluth, Arjen Schrijvers, Stefanie Thielman, Sam Suresh, Richard van Tilborg, Michael Snoeren</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Sarah Watz, Johan Van der Velde</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Stefanie is the new leader of the Exam Team, Arjen is the new Assistant Team Leader.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team is working to provide the next exam for Pisa.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam length stays to 90 minutes.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Operations Team sent Welcome Pack to JLPs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team is not working on a long-term strategy, but providing quick help to exam organisers</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team is working on the development environment for the Exam platform.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team is working on changing the way candidates can be associated with the JLPs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Certification Team noticed that there are some errors in the articles about the Certification Program published on the Joomla! Community Magazine, Richard will deal with the JCM Team to fix the issues.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 55 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 31, 2, 669, '2016-10-11 14:01:30', 669, '2016-10-12 01:16:25', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(345, 0, 16, 'Joomla! Certification Platform Team Meeting', 'joomla-certification-platform-team-meeting', '<p><em>Attendance: Sam Suresh, Michael Snoeren, Chris Keen</em></p>\r\n<p>Meeting notes published to the community:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sam Suresh welcomed Chris to the team</li>\r\n<li>Sam explained how the current platform is built and added current members as Administrators</li>\r\n<li>New exam will be setup to follow changes in the improvement plan and will be available for exam at PISA this weekend. This exam will be reviewed by Certification Team leaders before go live.</li>\r\n<li>Current exam will be archieved.</li>\r\n<li>Chris to explore the platform\'s backend system to be able to create new exams or manage exams in the future. </li>\r\n<li>Sam proposed new method on how a student is registered in the platform. Currently students needed to be registered by exam host one by one to create host-student relationship. The new proposed method will allow host to pick users from the Joomla! database and students can self register.</li>\r\n<li>Michael Snoeren to work in the new proposal.</li>\r\n<li>Sam advised members to keep safe all backups with password and to enable 2 factor authentications as these data contains sensitive information such as questions, answers and student data.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The certification team currently need new energetic people to contribute in various areas. If you commited to contribute, do contact us via <a>https://certification.joomla.org/contribute/volunteer</a></p>\r\n<p>The platform team members meet every Wednesday 9pm GMT+8.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 32, 1, 813, '2016-10-12 13:34:11', 0, '2016-10-12 13:48:15', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(346, 0, 18, 'Certification Exam Team 2016-10-13', 'meeting-minutes-certification-exam-team-2016-10-13', '<p>Attended by<br /><br />Claudia Weber-Lenck, Chris Keen, Andr&aacute;s R&aacute;tonyi, Stefanie Thielmann</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Meeting notes <br /><br />The exam questions for the Pisa exam are ready to be set up on the official platform. <br />Before the next exam (Pisa), a test will be run will be held by the Certification Steering Group team. <br /><br />The team is also working to set up a new system to maintain the questions and answers.. New volunteers are very much needed for maintaining the questions and for setting up a maintanance system (based on Joomla!)</p>\r\n<p>The certification team currently need new energetic people to contribute in various areas. If you commited to contribute, do contact us via <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/contribute/volunteer">https://certification.joomla.org/contribute/volunteer</a><a><br /><br /><br /></a></p>', NULL, 1, 33, 2, 766, '2016-10-12 18:58:47', 766, '2016-11-02 20:30:29', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(347, 0, 19, 'COT - Meeting notes - October 13, 2016', 'cot-meeting-notes-october-13-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-efeb5887-be19-b082-1e0e-770edc48ff65" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on October 13th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Luca Marzo, Oscar Ortiz, Pablo Pantoja, Richard van Tilborg, Arjen Schrijvers.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Johan Van der Velde, Todd Woodward, Andre Dreier.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick reported news from the last Steering meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JLPs received the Welcome Packs and the JLP badge Policy.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team worked hard to review the Exam and it&rsquo;s ready for the session in Pisa on Saturday.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team is working also on the tool to maintain questions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca worked on the ticket system during last weekend, cleaning up the list of pending tickets.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Richard will join Luca as Supervisor at JoomlaDay Italy.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Oscar will help the Platform Team as Developer, working with Michael at Certified Users Directory and then he will help Exam Team building the system to maintain questions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">COT will work closely with Richard and Marketing Team in order to change and improve the content and navigation systems of the Certification Website.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">CMT is looking for graphic designers, please apply using the following form and choosing &ldquo;Marketing Team&rdquo;: https://certification.joomla.org/contribute/volunteer</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Following some wrong information posted on the Joomla! Community Magazine, Certification Operations Team wants to highlight that in case of Community Events and JoomlaDays, there&rsquo;s a difference between the session organizer and the Supervisor. At events, only members approved by COT can supervise Exam Sessions. Generally session organizer is a different person from the Supervisor. About this, following in this report, COT publishes the list of upcoming exam sessions with approved Supervisors.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Community events:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Joomla! World Conference</strong> (Canada) with Sarah Watz as Supervisor (<strong>November 11</strong>, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>JoomlaDay Italy</strong> with Luca Marzo and Richard van Tilborg &nbsp;as Supervisors (<strong>November 12</strong>, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>JoomlaDay Austria</strong> with Stefanie Thielmann as Supervisor (<strong>December 2</strong>, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming Exam sessions at Joomla! Learning Partners:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Colt Engine in Pisa, Italy on <strong>October 15</strong>, 2016.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p>Meeting ends after 50 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 34, 1, 669, '2016-10-13 12:52:02', 0, '2016-10-13 12:53:14', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(348, 0, 49, 'Detalles publicaciÃ³n octubre 2016', 'detalles-publicacion-octubre-2016', '<p>Durante el mes de septiembre el equipo del Magazine de la Comunidad Joomla! estuvo trabajando en la reestructuraci&oacute;n de la publicaci&oacute;n con el &aacute;nimo de ofrecer contenidos m&aacute;s enfocados a la comunidad de habla hispana, para esto se cre&oacute; un nuevo repositorio de temas para la generaci&oacute;n de contenidos.</p>\r\n<p>Al d&iacute;a 15 de octubre se public&oacute; la edici&oacute;n del mes con seis art&iacute;culos en las &aacute;reas de administraci&oacute;n, comunidad, desarrollo, eventos y un art&iacute;culo de parte del Comit&eacute; Editorial con el fin de reforzar el grupo de autores del magazine.</p>\r\n<p>Un agradecimiento para Anibal S&aacute;nchez, Carlos Olivares, Oscar Ortiz y Ren&eacute; Blas que colaboraron para esta edici&oacute;n.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In September the Spanish JCM Team worked on a major restructuring to offer new contents focused on the Spanish speaking community. A topic repository was created to inspire known and new authors.</p>\r\n<p>On October 15th the monthly issue was published. It includes six articles covering the following topics: Management, Community, Development, Events and an article from the Editorial Board which calls for new authors.</p>\r\n<p>Special thanks to Anibal S&aacute;nchez, Carlos Olivares, Oscar Ortiz and Ren&eacute; Blas who contibuted to this issue.</p>', NULL, 1, 35, 1, 869, '2016-10-16 21:55:02', 0, '2016-10-16 22:00:37', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(349, 0, 17, 'Certification Marketing Team - Meeting Notes October 17, 2016', 'certification-marketing-team-meeting-notes-october', '<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Joomla! Certification Marketing Team (MT) meets every 2 weeks on monday at 20:00 PM CET. This meeting was held on October, 17th, 2016 on Glip.</span></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 16pt; margin-bottom: 4pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Team members</span></h3>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance:</span><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> &nbsp;Richard van Tilborg, Johan van der Velde, Luca Marzo, Andrea Kek&aacute;n, Adamzy Lee</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">:</span> Elisa Foltyn, Sarah Watz, Andrea Gentil, Rogelio Alvarado, Eric Lamy, Mike Veeckmans.</span></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 16pt; margin-bottom: 4pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Discussion Outline</span></h3>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Andrea Gentil is offline this meeting and this week she is working on the JoomlaDay list.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Richard asked Luca to give a short summary of the Supervisor Role in Pisa and what we can do as JCP MT.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Richard welcomes a new team member Andrea Kek&aacute;n and give her a short introduction about our tasks in the JCP.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Richard wants to use Crowdin a Management Platform for developers and website owners.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Andrea Kek&aacute;n is familiar with Crowdin and she will start with a new project for the JCP MT. She can ask Marc Antoine Thevenet or Mike Veeckmans for more information.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Website: Several people (Richard, Patrick, Luca and Andreas) &nbsp;worked on our website certification.joomla.org. They created a temporary subgroup.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Richard and Johan will create tasks and assign them to the JCP MT members.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Next meeting will be on: 31 october 2016 - from 20.00 to 21.00 our CET.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong style="font-weight: normal;">&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 13.3333px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Meeting ends after 70 minutes</span></p>', NULL, 1, 36, 1, 1202, '2016-10-17 20:30:42', 0, '2016-10-17 20:32:22', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(350, 0, 78, 'Certification Steering Meeting - October 18, 2016', 'certification-steering-meeting-october-18-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-643104de-d811-fc4a-224e-1d6d66949ace" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Steering Group meets every Tuesday at 2:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on October 18th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Sarah Watz, Patrick Jungbluth, Stefanie Thielman, Sam Suresh, Richard van Tilborg, Michael Snoeren</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Johan Van der Velde, Arjen Schrijvers</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Richard and Marketing Team worked improving the Certification website.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team welcome Andrea Kekan as designer.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team is working on the dev environment and obtained a private repository on Github.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team worked on statistics coming from the exam in Pisa.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca reported information about the exam session in Pisa last weekend. We have 2 more Certified Administrator after this session.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Meeting ends after 55 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 37, 1, 669, '2016-10-18 13:53:57', 0, '2016-10-18 13:54:23', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(351, 0, 16, 'Joomla! Certification Platform Team Meeting Notes 19 Oct', 'joomla-certification-platform-team-meeting-notes-1', '<p><em>Attendance: Sam Suresh, Michael Snoeren, Oscar Ortiz, Chris Keen, Luca Marzo<br /></em></p>\r\n<p>Meeting notes published to the community: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Exam at Pisa, Italy successful. No platform issues reported</li>\r\n<li>Sam already setup dev site and dev platform. These 2 source codes are available on Github private repo. Team members now can collaborate in this repo.</li>\r\n<li>Michael to work on JLP user selection function.</li>\r\n<li>Oscar to improve Certification Directory frontend.</li>\r\n<li>Chris to discuss with exam team on new exams/questions and setup in dev site. Dev site can be used as maintenance tool for questions/exams for now.</li>\r\n<li>Every exam restored to production site must be reported to Sam before allowing access to other teams.</li>\r\n<li>All issues related to platform must be reported via Report an Issue link that can be found at the footer of exam.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>Sam suggested new meeting time 6pm GMT+8 from next week onwards and all members agreed. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The platform team members meet every Wednesday 9pm GMT+8.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 38, 5, 813, '2016-10-19 13:44:20', 813, '2016-10-19 14:00:44', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(352, 0, 19, 'COT - Meeting notes - October 20, 2016', 'cot-meeting-notes-october-20-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-4025dfbc-e22a-2eca-0f6d-22145fd926ec" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on October 20th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Luca Marzo, Oscar Ortiz, Arjen Schrijvers, Sam Suresh.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Johan Van der Velde, Todd Woodward, Andre Dreier, Pablo Pantoja, Richard van Tilborg.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick reported news from the last Steering meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team is working on the Certification website in order to improve the UX.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">COT discussed about handling fees for Exam hosted at JoomlaDays and JUGs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">At the moment, due to undergoing changes, the Exam Platform doesn&rsquo;t allow people at JUGs and JoomlaDays to pay their seats directly via the Platform, so JUGs and JoomlaDays organizers must currently act as JLP, buying the exam seats for candidates. (This is a temporary measure).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay and JUGs organizers may apply as Service/Handling fee of maximum 10 EUR / 10 USD in order to cover the PayPal/Stripe fees while handling the payments. This is just to face the temporary &ldquo;limit&rdquo; of the platform. When the platform will be ready to allow people to pay directly for their seats, the service/handling fee won&rsquo;t be allowed anymore.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Steering group will discuss again on the above measures at next meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Community events:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Joomla! World Conference (Canada) with Sarah Watz as Supervisor (November 11, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay Italy with Luca Marzo and Richard van Tilborg &nbsp;as Supervisors (November 12, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay Austria with Stefanie Thielmann as Supervisor (December 2, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 55 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 39, 1, 669, '2016-10-20 12:56:27', 0, '2016-10-20 12:57:13', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(353, 41, 0, 'PLT Meeting - October 20, 2016', 'plt-meeting-october-20-2016', '<h3 id="docs-internal-guid-b17af98b-e3a4-e5ea-42db-a7ef0e912db1" dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Presents</span>: Javier, Chris, Marco, Luca, Robert, Tessa, George, Viktor, Roland</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: -</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Time</span>: &nbsp;20:00 CET</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Total time of the meeting</span>:&nbsp; 110 minutes</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Previous meeting minutes</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="leadership/production-leadership-team/reports/336-plt-meeting-september-29-2016">https://volunteers.joomla.org/leadership/production-leadership-team/reports/336-plt-meeting-september-29-2016</a></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion outline</h3>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Budget update (Robert)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Robert shared the details after the Financial Workgroup Meeting in New York, October 6-7. Data will be published by OSM as soon as possible. PLT approved an Automated Testing sprint at the end of the year.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">CMS Release Team (George)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">CMS Release Team is working as expected. The 3.6.3 release process has been completed properly, even if the release has an issue with the Two Factor Authentication. We are likely to release 3.6.4 in the next week to deal with this.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">GSOC Shareable drafted content (Roland)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">PLT is currently voting about merging the PR. Voting process will end on October 31, 2016. Results will be published.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/12009">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/12009</a></p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">GSOC Improved Multilingual (Javier)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">PLT is currently voting about merging the PR. Voting process will end on October 31, 2016. Results will be published.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/12009">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/12009</a></p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Issue with Unlimited private repositories (Tessa)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Michael Babker noticed that is not possible to create more than 10 private repositories within the Joomla! Organization on GitHub, even if the project received unlimited private repositories. Tessa will try to contact Github support to figure out this.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Report from JSST (Viktor)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">JSST welcomed two new members: Yves Hoppe and Peter Martin. Team re-activated mailing lists to forward vulnerability reports to all team members. Team is working to some patches that will be shipped with 3.6.4 soon.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Joomla! 3.7 (George)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Routing has now been fully merged. We are likely to release our first alpha in the next few weeks depending on a final code review of Custom fields.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Joomla! 4 (George)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Joomla 4 has continued to make progress with more code removal and refactoring. I have started to turn attention to what features we want to actually demonstrate to attract users to upgrade.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">J4 templates are under heavy work. We are still working in a private repository but hope to make that public in mid-late December.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Joomla X (Marco)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We worked on extending testability &amp; test coverage. Big part on command line interface coverage, We are using docker containers for testing. Extra effort put into documenting the code and workings.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Reports from Automated Testing (Javier)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Selenium 3.0 <a href="https://seleniumhq.wordpress.com/2016/10/13/selenium-3-0-out-now/">https://seleniumhq.wordpress.com/2016/10/13/selenium-3-0-out-now/</a> has been released. This will affect our acceptance tests, we are working on updating our Selenium Server Standalone library: <a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/selenium-server-standalone">https://github.com/joomla-projects/selenium-server-standalone</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The Automated Testing Working Group coordinators together with Robert Jacobi are organising an Automated Testing Code Sprint that will take place in Germany from the 9th to the 11th of December.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The Automated Testing Working Group has decided to have two Glip groups, one for general testing debates and one specific for the active members of the team. Members not active will be moved to the honor roll.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Facebook Authentication plugin (Luca)</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Following the PLT decision, Luca created a repository on Github to host the code of the Facebook Authentication plugin developed and maintained by Nicholas K. Dionysopoulos and will be released as Official Extensions. Code is available here: <a href="https://github.com/joomla-extensions/facebook-auth">https://github.com/joomla-extensions/facebook-auth</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The plugin is almost ready to be released. Component translation is managed by Community Translation Team through Crowdin. Facebook Authentication plugin will be available for Joomla! 3.7 and is dependant from the PR #12061 that needs to be tested and merged in 3.7 codebase. Please help testing <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/12061">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/12061</a></p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">CREDITS file out of date</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">This topic came out in the CMS Maintenance Team. The CREDITS file is out of date and it includes all the contributors before the migration to Github. <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/commits/staging/installation/CREDITS">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/commits/staging/installation/CREDITS</a> . PLT decided to remove the content from the file and move it to a page in the Joomla! Docs. Credits file will include a link to that page.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">PHP-FIG representative</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Even if Robert Deutz stepped down from PLT, he will still serve as PHP FIG representative, since he&rsquo;s Team Leader of the CMS Release Team.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Pizza Bugs and Fun</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Roland is organizing a PBF in The Netherlands on November 4th. Luca will try to arrange a PBF at the end of november / early december in Italy.</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Votes Summary</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">During this month, PLT had the following votes:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Automated Testing Code Sprint 2016 (Passed)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Improving menu item workflow in Joomla! GSOC (Voting process ends on october 31)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Recording action logs GSOC (Voting process ends on october 31)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">Removing out of date content from CREDITS file and moving it to a JDocs page (Passed)</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL, 1, 40, 2, 669, '2016-10-20 19:49:54', 669, '2016-10-21 07:53:51', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(354, 3, 0, 'CLT Meeting Minutes - October 13 at 19:00:00  UTC', 'clt-meeting-minutes-october-13-at-19-00-00-utc', '<h3 dir="ltr">Participants:</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Mike Veeckmans (MV)<br />Sandra Thevenet (ST)<br />Rowan Hoskyns Abrahall (RHA)<br />Cliff Pfeifer (CP)<br />Sander Potjer (SP)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Apologies: Anibal Sanchez, David Jardin, Johan Janssens, Helvecio da Silva</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">EVENTS TEAM</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">We will put together a post event survey requesting numbers, sponsors etc so we can gather a better picture of Jday Events and ensure all events have published financial reporting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">JWC</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">As this is a CLT budget line, we need to be made aware of any proposed contracts for next year before they are signed. We will be contacting Sarah Watz and the JWC team to ensure this oversight takes place.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">FORUM</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Cliff steps down as Liaison, Mike Veeckmans takes his place. &nbsp;Introductions have been made formally and this is now in place.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">CDN and Footer menu have been updated and site has been switched to https</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">JCM</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">An article regarding the JCP was written by a CLT member without the team&rsquo;s permission or knowledge. Articles had to be unpublished which put a great amount of strain on the JCP and JCM teams unnecessarily. &nbsp;We must make sure this doesn&rsquo;t happen again.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JCM will look to doing more crafted social media posts rather than relying on pure automated system generated posts.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">JED</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JED Team has taken steps to implement the new Joomla Update System requirement - <a href="https://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/faq-about-joomla-update-system-requirement">https://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/faq-about-joomla-update-system-requirement</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JED Team has cleared ticket queues and fixed reported bugs (AS)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">JOOMLA.ORG</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">About Joomla! Page to be updated to correctly display the 3 download options (Download - Demo - Joomla.com) MV and ST to work on implementing this.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Press section will be added to site to contain press releases.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">When new downloads site is launched current (out of date) video on homepage will be removed and the position used to highlight the new downloads site. &nbsp;Moving forwards this position will be used to highlight any important element, event or project that is relevant at the time.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>JRD</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Geolocation issues are still ongoing - see this github thread for more information - <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-websites/issues/154">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-websites/issues/154</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>VJO</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Birthday field to be added to volunteer&rsquo;s profile (day and month only)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Export of Volunteers to be provided to Marketing.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Updated VJO for transition has been put up for testing, has been tested and is ready for Transition.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>VEL</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">This site is an official project team hosted on a project server and as such is subject to the same oversight and requirements of any other team. &nbsp;We will be looking at ways to improve the look and feel of the site.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Webmaster Team</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Downloads site will be launched at the end of October/beginning of November. &nbsp;All properties with links to the old downloads page will need to be updated. &nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">CDN menu and footer have been updated in the template repo. &nbsp;Ready for pulling when the launch has happened. &nbsp;Properties not using this will need to do the update manually.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Social Team</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Will be starting a Thank You campaign to volunteers shortly.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Joom.la url shortner issues are still being worked on.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">MWG</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Allocated some budget to JET to allow JET to run.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Mascot call has been launched.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">3.7 Teaser copy is in progress with imagery starting soon.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 41, 1, 1035, '2016-10-23 10:34:00', 0, '2016-10-23 10:37:49', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(355, 0, 14, 'October 2016', 'october-2016', '<p>Discussion on unreportable items.</p>\r\n<p>Discussion on reporting issues with hosting.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Issues with missing reports and contacts from volunteers portal.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Response to recruitment drive</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 42, 3, 568, '2016-10-23 20:01:32', 568, '2016-10-23 20:05:06', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(356, 0, 78, 'Certification Steering Meeting - October 25, 2016', 'certification-steering-meeting-october-25-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-9ffa79bc-fc10-4b3b-ca5b-88f6457e25ed" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Steering Group meets every Tuesday at 2:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on October 25th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Sarah Watz, Patrick Jungbluth, Sam Suresh, Richard van Tilborg, Michael Snoeren, Stefanie Thielman.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Johan Van der Velde, Arjen Schrijvers.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team is working on the exam platform and applied many improvements.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team created a Demo exam in order to allow candidates to understand how the exam environment works.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team published a new Learning Guide.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team is still working on the website in order to improve the navigation.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">A small subteam has been created to work on the tool to maintain and translate questions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 35 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 43, 1, 669, '2016-10-25 13:38:32', 0, '2016-10-25 13:38:58', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(357, 0, 16, 'Joomla! Certification Platform Team 26 Oct 2016', 'joomla-certification-platform-team-26-oct-2016', '<p><em>Attendees: Sam Suresh, Michael Snoeren, Oscar Ortiz</em></p>\r\n<p><em>Absence: Chris Keen<br /></em></p>\r\n<p><img src="images/reports/tour.png" alt="tour" width="563" height="229" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Meeting notes published to the community:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Oscar worked on CSS to improve certification directory. </li>\r\n<li>Michael created a new view for user pickup from User Table. This improvement will create a process change and JLP/JoomlaDay not require to register candidates for exam. Candidates can self register. As this breaks some other process, team to work on this this week. </li>\r\n<li>Sam worked on Demo exam to provide a demo of how the exam system work for the public. It will be available from next week onwards. </li>\r\n<li>There is a bug the certification directory that prevent public from reading the user avatar. Oscar and Sam to work on a fix this week.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The platform team members meet every Wednesday 6pm GMT+8.</p>', NULL, 1, 44, 1, 813, '2016-10-26 10:33:33', 0, '2016-10-26 10:41:55', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(358, 0, 18, 'Certification Exam Team 2016-10-26', 'meeting-minutes-certification-exam-team-2016-10-26', '<p>Attended by<br /><br />Claudia Weber-Lenck, Chris Keen, Rick Spaan, Stefanie Thielmann</p>\r\n<p>Absent</p>\r\n<p>Arjen Schrijvers, Andr&aacute;s R&aacute;tonyi</p>\r\n<p>Meeting notes</p>\r\n<p>Creating the next exams for the JWC and Rome is our goal for the next weeks.<br />The team discussed the new maintenance system and the process that will be followed.<br />The team will have two focuses from now on, the maintenance system and the exam preparation.<br /><a><br /></a></p>\r\n<p>To all participants of the next exams - good luck and be prepared ;-)</p>', NULL, 1, 45, 2, 766, '2016-10-26 19:28:20', 766, '2016-11-02 20:30:20', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(359, 0, 19, 'COT - Meeting notes - October 27, 2016', 'cot-meeting-notes-october-27-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-3f821bb6-061c-2491-b282-eb070c9a6420" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on October 27th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Luca Marzo, Oscar Ortiz, Todd Woodward.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Johan Van der Velde, Andre Dreier, Pablo Pantoja, Richard van Tilborg, Arjen Schrijvers.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick reported news from the last Steering meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team is working on the Platform and created a Demo Exam to show candidates how the system works.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Oscar is working on the Certified Users Directory, improving the UX and responsivity.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team published a brand-new Learning Guide for the Joomla! Administrator Exam: <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/exams/administrator-tasks-learning-list">https://certification.joomla.org/exams/administrator-tasks-learning-list</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">In order to avoid students being charged for payment handling fees, Steering Group decided that in order to cover payment handling fees from JUG and JoomlaDay organisers, students will continue paying the published amount for the Exam and CT will provide organisers a lower price for Exam seats. This is a temporary measure that will be deleted during the next month, when users can finally pay themselves for their exam seats.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Community events:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Joomla! World Conference</strong> (Canada) with Sarah Watz as Supervisor (November 13, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>JoomlaDay Italy</strong> with Luca Marzo and Richard van Tilborg as Supervisors (November 12, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>JoomlaDay Austria</strong> with Stefanie Thielmann as Supervisor (December 2, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 25 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 46, 1, 669, '2016-10-27 12:27:36', 0, '2016-10-27 12:28:22', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(360, 0, 44, 'JED Team Meeting 28th October 2016', 'jed-team-meeting-28th-october-2016', '<p>Today the Joomla Extensions Directory (JED) team met at 2pm GMT via Glip to discuss our progress of current tasks.</p>\r\n<p>In attendance: Matthew Baylor, Jaz Parkyn, Luca Marzo, Anibal Sanchez, Martin Mueller</p>\r\n<p>Statistics for the month of October 2016</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Extension Submissions: 58 submitted, 36 processed</li>\r\n<li>Ticket Submission: 214 submitted, 196 processed</li>\r\n<li>Reviews: 415 submitted</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>A small reminder that extensions with call-home functions are only permitted to be listed on JED if:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The extension can work normally without a developer server connection</li>\r\n<li>It\'s possible to install the extension without a call home</li>\r\n<li>The extension is allowed to phone home for version checks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>JED Development Environment</strong></p>\r\n<p>We have started the process of amending com_jed to use the core mailing function and relay the emails through SendGrid.</p>\r\n<p>The IP Detection script for reviews still has a few issues that need to be ironed out. If you experience any issues, please let us know by creating an issue on JIRA: <a href="https://joomlaextensionsdirectory.atlassian.net">https://joomlaextensionsdirectory.atlassian.net</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Call for Volunteers</strong></p>\r\n<p>The JED team is currently looking for more volunteers to assist with processing tickets and extensions. If this is something you are interested in, please fill out the below form:</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://extensions.joomla.org/volunteer-application">https://extensions.joomla.org/volunteer-application</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Updates to Listing Requirements</strong></p>\r\n<p>A reminder that all extensions listed on the JED will soon be required to use the Joomla Update System. This will help to ensure that site owners are always notified of when a new version of their installed extensions is available. Keeping extensions up to date can help to improve security.</p>\r\n<p>This change is a mandatory requirement and checks will be added to the JED Checker. The error code will be: US1 - update sites not present in xml file. This new requirement will come into force on January 10th 2017.</p>\r\n<p>**With regards to extensions already listed on JED, they will not be unpublished if they are not in compliance with this new requirement. Instead a popup warning will be shown to users when clicking the Download button, informing them that the extension doesn\'t support update servers and therefore must be updated manually.**</p>\r\n<p>Further information can be found in the minutes from 1st July 2016.</p>\r\n<p>The JED knowledgebase article covering update server implementation is available from the below link.<br /><a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/joomla-update-system-requirement">http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/joomla-update-system-requirement</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Contributing to JED</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you find any bugs or would like to suggest an improvement, please find the issue on our JIRA Issue Tracker. Your opinion could make a significant impact on the Extensions Directory.</p>\r\n<p>To be added to our Glip developer chat, please send an email to jaz.parkyn (at) extensions.joomla.org asking for access. You will see important tasks to the right, and we will discuss general issues there. (Specific issues will be discussed within JIRA). Also, JIRA integrates with our chat system, so you can easily see new issues and replies to issues right in our chat system.</p>\r\n<p>To find out more about the JED development process and how you can contribute, please see these pages:<br />- <a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/contributing-code-to-the-jed">http://extensions.joomla.org/support/knowledgebase/item/contributing-code-to-the-jed</a> <br />- <a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/fun-in-jed-bug-smashing-and-feature-development">http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/fun-in-jed-bug-smashing-and-feature-development</a> <br />- <a href="http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/how-to-collaborate-and-improve-our-jed-jab16-barcelona">http://extensions.joomla.org/blog/item/how-to-collaborate-and-improve-our-jed-jab16-barcelona</a></p>\r\n<p>The next JED team meeting will take place on 25th November 2016 at the same time.</p>', NULL, 1, 47, 1, 695, '2016-10-28 14:46:09', 0, '2016-10-28 14:51:15', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(361, 0, 78, 'Certification Team Meeting - November 1, 2016', 'certification-team-meeting-november-1-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-bceaec3a-205f-4bda-69d3-4ccef25e61d8" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Group meets monthly each first Tuesday at 2:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on November 1, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Patrick Jungbluth, Sam Suresh, Richard van Tilborg, Michael Snoeren, Stefanie Thielman, Oscar Ortiz, Claudia Weber-Lenck.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team enrolled all the JLPs in the platform.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team will arrange a Welcome meeting for JLPs to explain how the system works and how to use the Exam Platform.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team is working on the maintenance system for the questions.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam team provided also some timing about the next steps.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Operations Team enrolled all the JLPs in the certification website in order to allow them to use Support System and Exam Calendar.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team discussed also about the future exams.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team decided to start adopting milestones for each subteam.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>Meeting ends after 50 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 48, 1, 669, '2016-11-01 14:51:09', 0, '2016-11-01 14:51:45', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(362, 0, 13, '1st of November 2016 User Groups Team (JUG) meeting report', '1th-of-november-2016-user-groups-team-jug-meeting', '<p dir="ltr">In attendance:</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Djamel Kherbi</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Jenn Gress</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rowan Hoskyns-Abrahall</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Bruce Valle</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Apologies:</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Brian Ronnow</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">No Shows:</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Eric Lamy</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Duke Speer</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marco Richter</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">We had our bi-monthly meeting first meeting for the month of November, helded &nbsp;from 19 pm to 20 pm CET on Google hangout, the following items were discussed.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">1- review and updates on JUG pending listing, Bruce is working on a new listing from Malaysia and an update listing from Joomla user Group Strasbourg (France).</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Djamel will follow up on the listing update from Kaduna (Nigeria)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Jenn is working on a listing from Russia.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">2- &nbsp;Joomla user group Swag will be ready for the JWC 16 in Vancouver, a new registred logo for &nbsp;Joomla user group is coming soon</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The next meeting will be on the held on the 15th of November, Djamel will Lead the meeting and Jennifer Gress will take minutes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>', NULL, 1, 49, 2, 468, '2016-11-01 21:45:29', 468, '2016-11-01 21:52:59', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(363, 0, 15, 'Downloads Site Launched, JoomlaCode Shutdown Update', 'downloads-site-launched-joomlacode-shutdown-update', '<p>Earlier this week we transitioned all downloads for Joomla! to our <a href="https://www.joomla.org/announcements/general-news/5691-joomla-downloads-website.html">new downloads portal</a>; this includes the file repositories and our update system. &nbsp;This completes the initial build out of the downloads site and we will soon begin work on the next phases of this large project, which includes integrating all of the language packages for Joomla! as well as our official extensions.</p>\r\n<p>In line with our plans to retire JoomlaCode, we have now unpublished all of the CMS\' data from our JoomlaCode project. &nbsp;All of the packages for every Joomla! release can be found on our new downloads portal. &nbsp;All of the issues that were logged at JoomlaCode can be found in a <a href="https://developer.joomla.org/joomlacode-archive.html">static archive on the Developer Network</a>. &nbsp;Unfortunately, we have been unable to configure the server to redirect traffic to these new sources, we will continue looking into ways to accomplish these redirects.</p>', NULL, 1, 50, 1, 447, '2016-11-02 16:08:28', 0, '2016-11-02 16:18:49', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(364, 0, 18, 'Certification Exam Team 2016-11-02 ', 'meeting-minutes-certification-exam-team-2016-11-02', '<p>This is a very fast one:</p>\r\n<p>Claudia Weber-Lenck, Arjen Schrijvers and Stefanie Thielmann</p>\r\n<p>discussed the new process for the maintenance system</p>\r\n<p>this week the team also worked buissy on the exam questions</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 51, 2, 766, '2016-11-02 20:26:38', 766, '2016-11-02 20:30:09', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(365, 0, 19, 'COT - Meeting notes - November 3, 2016', 'cot-meeting-notes-november-3-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-f9cf1791-2a67-6d4d-f85a-e6bd94faf28f" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on November 3rd, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Oscar Ortiz, Richard van Tilborg</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Patrick Jungbluth, Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Johan Van der Velde, Andre Dreier, Pablo Pantoja, Arjen Schrijvers, Todd Woodward.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca reported news from the last Steering meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team arranged a welcome meeting for JLPs, explaining them how to use the Exam Platform and the JLP Dashboard to buy and assign exam seats, providing them also a short webinar.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Oscar is working together with Andrea Kekan on the Certified Users Directory, improving the UX and responsivity.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">The JCP website working group is working to improve the certification website.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JLPs started planning their sessions and publishing them on the Exam Calendar: <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/exams/calendar">https://certification.joomla.org/exams/calendar</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team published the following disclaimer on top of the exam page:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">The Joomla! Administrator Exam is based on a clean Joomla! installation (downloaded from<a href="http://joomla.org"> joomla.org</a>) using the default language (en-GB), the default editor (TinyMCE), default template (Protostar) and settings, without any 3rd party extension or customisation.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Community events:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>JoomlaDay Italy</strong> with Luca Marzo and Richard van Tilborg as Supervisors (November 12, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Joomla! World Conference</strong> (Canada) with Sarah Watz as Supervisor (November 13, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>JoomlaDay Austria</strong> with Stefanie Thielmann as Supervisor (December 2, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Joomla! Learning Partners:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>R2H</strong> - The Netherlands - November 8, 2016</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Pulsar Informatique</strong> - France - November 21, 2016</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Octopoos</strong> - France - November 22, 2016</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 30 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 52, 1, 669, '2016-11-03 13:36:20', 0, '2016-11-03 13:37:24', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(366, 0, 78, 'Certification Steering Meeting - November 08, 2016', 'certification-steering-meeting-november-08-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-d6d87621-4473-4e00-6fba-8edb085693b6" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Steering Group meets every Tuesday at 2:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on November 08, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Sam Suresh, Patrick Jungbluth, Stefanie Thielman.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Johan Van der Velde, Arjen Schrijvers, Sarah Watz, Richard van Tilborg, Michael Snoeren.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team is working on the exam review.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team is working also on the maintenance system. A plan will be proposed at the end of november.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team had a webinar with JLPs to explain how the system works</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team worked on the feature that allow candidates to self register and JLPs/Session organizers to pick candidates from the database.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team will provide a link for people at JWC to buy the exam seats.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Operations Team is working on screening new applications from JLPs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 55 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 53, 1, 669, '2016-11-08 14:59:35', 0, '2016-11-08 15:00:05', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(367, 0, 16, 'Joomla! Certification Platform Team 9 Nov 2016', 'joomla-certification-platform-team-9-nov-2016', '<p>Attendees: Sam Suresh, Michael Snoeren, Oscar Ortiz, Chris Keen, Luca Marzo<br /><br />Meeting notes published to the community:<br /><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sam reported news from steering meeting.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Michael\'s new enhancements on picking users directly from db is pushed to live site.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sam conducted a webinar to all JLP on how to handle the system. This webinar was recorded and made available for new comers.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Oscar to sync CSS enhancements to certified directory on dev site for review<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sam to setup new exam and make available direct purchase and self enrolment by end users. This will be used in JWC 2016 and Rome. The link to buy exams will be avalaible to public on Thursday onwards. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Sam to work on printable certificates and make available before JWC 2016 exam session. <br /><br />The platform team members meet every Wednesday 6pm GMT+8.</p>', NULL, 1, 54, 1, 813, '2016-11-09 11:28:18', 0, '2016-11-09 11:29:31', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(368, 0, 19, 'COT - Meeting notes - November 10, 2016', 'cot-meeting-notes-november-10-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-f998cb6a-4e71-9875-732c-ef2eec5ddee9" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on November 10th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Patrick Jungbluth, Oscar Ortiz, Richard van Tilborg, Todd Woodward.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Johan Van der Velde, Andre Dreier, Pablo Pantoja, Arjen Schrijvers.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick reported news from the last Steering meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">The JCP website working group is still working to improve the certification website.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JLPs started planning their sessions and publishing them on the Exam Calendar: <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/exams/calendar">https://certification.joomla.org/exams/calendar</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Oscar will serve as co-Supervisor for the Exam Session at Joomla! World Conference.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Candidates for the session at JWC can buy their exam seats at: <a href="https://exam.joomla.org/index.php/jwc-2016">https://exam.joomla.org/index.php/jwc-2016</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">People at JoomlaDays and JUGs will be able to buy exam seats for themselves directly via the Exam Platform.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Community events:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay Italy with Luca Marzo and Richard van Tilborg as Supervisors (November 12, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Joomla! World Conference (Canada) with Sarah Watz as Supervisor (November 13, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay Austria with Stefanie Thielmann as Supervisor (December 2, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Joomla! Learning Partners:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Pulsar Informatique - France - November 21, 2016</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Octopoos - France - November 22, 2016</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 30 minutes.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Joomla! Learning Partners</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Currently we have 23 Joomla! Learning Partners coming from Germany, France, The Netherlands, Italy, Austria, Croatia, Spain, Nigeria, Botswana, Norway, Malaysia and India.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you want to know more about Joomla! Learning Partners (JLPs) please visit <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/jlp/joomla-learning-partners">https://certification.joomla.org/jlp/joomla-learning-partners</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you want to apply as JLP, please start your qualification process at: <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/jlp/jlp-application-form">https://certification.joomla.org/jlp/jlp-application-form</a></p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Pending applications</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Here&rsquo;s a detailed report about applications as JLP still pending completion, divided by &ldquo;status&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Ready to sign (they have just to sign the Contracts): JLP-01, JLP-31, JLP-81.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Pending (missing information, details, pictures, documents): JLP-03, JLP-05, JLP-08, JLP-09, JLP-12, JLP-13, JLP-15, JLP-18, JLP-19, JLP-20, JLP-23, JLP-24, JLP-25, JLP-26, JLP-27, JLP-28, JLP-32, JLP-33, JLP-36, JLP-37, JLP-39, JLP-40, JLP-44, JLP-47, JLP-54, JLP-56, JLP-57, JLP-58, JLP-61, JLP-62, JLP-65, JLP-66, JLP-68, JLP-79, JLP-82.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Rejected (after being 6 months in the &ldquo;pending status&rdquo;): JLP-39, JLP-45, JLP-46.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All the applications that are currently marked as Ready to Sign, Interviewed or Pending will be automatically rejected on December 31, 2016 without any further notice.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you applied as JLP and you can find your application ID in the list above, please contact the COT at certification@community.joomla.org or open a ticket at https://certification.joomla.org/support</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The Certification Operations Team will be glad to help you finalising your application process.</p>', NULL, 1, 55, 1, 669, '2016-11-10 13:34:13', 0, '2016-11-10 13:34:41', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(369, 0, 49, 'Detalles publicaciÃ³n noviembre 2016', 'detalles-publicacion-noviembre-2016', '<p style="word-wrap: break-word;">Durante el mes de octubre el equipo del Magazine de la Comunidad Joomla! estuvo trabajando en la promoci&oacute;n del magazine con el fin de encontrar nuevos autores.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="word-wrap: break-word;">El d&iacute;a 10 de noviembre se public&oacute; la edici&oacute;n del mes con seis art&iacute;culos en las &aacute;reas de comunidad, desarrollo, &iquest;sab&iacute;as que? y dos art&iacute;culos de parte del Comit&eacute; Editorial.</p>\r\n<p style="word-wrap: break-word;">Un agradecimiento para Esteban Turcios, Leonel Cant&oacute;n, Lul&uacute; Garibay, Paola G&oacute;mez, Ren&eacute; Blas y Tito Alvarez,que colaboraron para esta edici&oacute;n.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="word-wrap: break-word;">In October the Spanish JCM Team worked&nbsp;on the promotion of the magazine in order to find new authors.</p>\r\n<p style="word-wrap: break-word;">On October 10 the monthly issue was published. It includes six articles covering the following topics: Community, Development and an article from the Editorial Board which calls for new authors.</p>\r\n<p style="word-wrap: break-word;">Special thanks to Esteban Turcios, Leonel Cant&oacute;n, Lul&uacute; Garibay, Paola G&oacute;mez, Ren&eacute; Blas y Tito Alvarezwho contibuted to this issue.</p>', NULL, 1, 56, 1, 869, '2016-11-13 01:57:28', 0, '2016-11-13 02:11:07', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(370, 0, 17, 'Certification Marketing Team - Meeting Notes November 14, 2016', 'certification-marketing-team-meeting-notes-novembe', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-781e367c-670b-e311-1ca0-f3bf34a4d513" dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">The Joomla! Certification Marketing Team (MT) meets every 2 weeks on Monday at 20:00 PM CET. This meeting was held on November, 14th, 2016 on Glip.</span></p>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 16pt; margin-bottom: 4pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Team members</span></h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #ff9900; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">In attendance</span><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">: &nbsp;Richard van Tilborg, Andrea Kek&aacute;n, Adamzy Lee, Andrea Gentil.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #ff9900; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Absents</span><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">: Elisa Foltyn, Sarah Watz, Rogelio Alvarado, Eric Lamy, Mike Veeckmans, Johan van der Velde, Luca Marzo.</span></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 16pt; margin-bottom: 4pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Discussion Outline</span></h3>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Richard asked Andrea K. to give an update about styles of the Certified Users Directory. Changes will be implemented by Oscar this week after a bug fix. She checks if they also can use responsive tables.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Website: Several people (Richard, Patrick, Johan, Luca and Andreas) are working on our website certification.joomla.org. They created a temporary subgroup.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Andrea G. worked on the calendar issues and archive issue. She will work on the Social Media plan again this week.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Richard asked Adamzy for info in Cote d\'Ivore for Certification Exam price. He&rsquo;s doing some more research because an exam price of $154 doesn&rsquo;t feel right.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Ecuador price will be determined too by Richard, based on Andrea K.&rsquo;s information.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">We are late with publishing news by miscommunication but will catch up this week.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Richard gave a summary of the exam at JoomlaDay Italy. 5 out of 11 passed with good scores. He has learned a lot in Rome and about language barriers and the Community. We are now going to find \'bridge builders\' that help the JCP to become a success in each country. We will start doing that by providing an even better Learning Guide for people that do not want to participate in training by JLPs (let\'s see them as semi-professionals that also mainly visit JUGs to learn about Joomla!). Besides that we want to position JLPs as training partners for professionals. There are two groups. One is a group that wants to improve their skills with good guidance and is ready to pay for that. The another group is people that do not need a long training, but more like a \'wake up training\' to refresh their memory about the Joomla! core features.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Next meeting will be on 28 November 2016 - from 20.00 to 21.00 our CET.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 2.38452; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as a reference.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Meeting ends after 70 minutes.</span></p>', NULL, 1, 57, 2, 1459, '2016-11-15 08:11:41', 1459, '2016-11-15 08:42:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(371, 0, 78, 'Certification Steering Meeting - November 15, 2016', 'certification-steering-meeting-november-15-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-6c83a088-687f-95cf-35b9-1b7fa4dcf600" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Steering Group meets every Tuesday at 2:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on November 15, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Sam Suresh, Patrick Jungbluth, Stefanie Thielman, Richard van Tilborg, Sarah Watz, Michael Snoeren.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Johan Van der Velde, Arjen Schrijvers.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Sarah reported her experience with the Certification at Joomla! World Conference.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Luca and Richard reported their experience with Certification at JoomlaDay Italy.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Marketing Team is working on the website and improving the learning guide.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Richard suggested to build &ldquo;bridges&rdquo; between Certification Program and Local Communities, these bridges are represented by Regional Coordinators.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Operations Team will work to enroll Regional Coordinators as soon as possible.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team is happy with the results of the latest sessions and is working on the maintenance system.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">We have 23 Joomla! Learning Partners coming from Germany, France, The Netherlands, Italy, Austria, Croatia, Spain, Nigeria, Botswana, Norway, Malaysia and India.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Operations Team brought to Steering the discussion about Exams at JUGs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform Team will provide automatically certificates to Joomla! Learning Partners certifying their status as JLP. Certificates will be issued via the Platform and will have a unique and verifiable serial number.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 60 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 58, 1, 669, '2016-11-15 14:58:51', 0, '2016-11-15 14:59:25', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(372, 0, 13, '15 November 2016 JUG Team Notes/Minutes', '15-november-2016-jug-team-notes-minutes', '<p><strong>In Attendance:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Djamel Kherbi<br />Jenn Gress<br />Rowan Hoskyns-Abrahall<br />Brian Ronnow<br />Duke Speer</p>\r\n<p><strong>Apologies:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Eric Lamy (Traveling)<br />Bruce Valle (Still in Vancouver/Travelling)</p>\r\n<p>Went over new and pending JUG listings. Some new ones from Italy as a result of the festival there and a few others.</p>\r\n<p>Rowan talked to us about the Italy event (JoomlaDay or Festival). Good stuff and changes happening there which is graet. Jenn talked to us about JWC16 and the Joomla In Action session which reactivated the Vancouver JUG and opened the way for 2-3 new jugs when they have a chance to find second contacts and get their sites ready, etc. Good session. Pleased.</p>\r\n<p>We approved a simple and streamlined JUG logo (thank you Rowan and the other person who helped with this!).</p>\r\n<p>Rowan resolved issues with the meetup modules/permission issues. Thank you, Rowan.</p>\r\n<p>Discussed ACY and ticket system...just checking in with each other on it to make sure we\'re all on the same page.</p>\r\n<p>We talked about certification too and how we can help the JUGs - Jenn is asking her JUG if they want us to host a certification in our area tomorrow night at the meetup.</p>\r\n<p>We talked about beginning to plan and discuss next years budget too. Draft is started already.</p>\r\n<p>Next meeting 6 December 2016.</p>', NULL, 1, 59, 2, 535, '2016-11-15 20:35:01', 535, '2016-11-15 20:50:23', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(373, 0, 23, 'Meeting and Vote for Team Leader  Nov 2016', 'meeting-and-vote-for-team-leader-nov-2016', '<p>On Nov 5, 2016 an email was sent from the Transition Team to the GWG to prepare for the transition process and to hold elections for Team Leader.&nbsp; On Nov 9, 2016 an email was sent to all team members Cindy Boater, Ronni Christensen, Crystal Dionysopoulos, Rod Martin, Paul Orwig, Radek Suski linking to a form to vote for Team Leader and Assistant Team Leader.&nbsp; The voting was open from Nov 9, 2016 through Nov 12, 2016.</p>\r\n<p>The results of the voting was to have Jennifer Marriott continue as Team Leader and for Cindy Boatner to continue as Assistant Team Leader.</p>\r\n<p>Ronni Christensen and Rod Martin chose to not take part in the voting and were moved to the honor roll.&nbsp; Their contribution to the team has been appreciated.</p>\r\n<p>The remaining team members: Cindy Boater, Crystal Dionysopoulos, Paul Orwig, Radek Suski and Jennifer Marriott met on Nov 14th via Glip to affirm the mission and purpose of the GWG:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;- To take on challenges and provide solutions regarding Governance, Community Standards and Accountability.<br />&nbsp;- To provide assistance to have a well governed, accountable, safe, vibrant Joomla community and Joomla leadership now and in the future.<br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 60, 2, 663, '2016-11-17 03:54:05', 663, '2016-11-17 04:17:49', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(374, 0, 19, 'COT - Meeting notes - November 17, 2016', 'cot-meeting-notes-november-17-2016', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-bb2a3f37-729a-2236-31dc-b90087573e82" dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on November 17th, 2016 on Glip.</p>\r\n<div dir="ltr">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Team members</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">In attendance</span>: Luca Marzo, Patrick Jungbluth, Oscar Ortiz, Arjen Schrijvers, Richard van Tilborg.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Absents</span>: Chris Keen, Hector Mansilla, Johan Van der Velde, Andre Dreier, Pablo Pantoja, Todd Woodward.</p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Discussion Outline</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick reported news from the last Steering meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Patrick reported also about the two sessions held last weekend at JoomlaDay Italy and Joomla! World Conference.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team wants to congratulate with all the new Joomla! Certified Administrators.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">COT will enroll Regional Coordinators in the next 2 weeks.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team will work redefining the role of Regional Coordinators that will serve as &ldquo;bridges&rdquo; between the Program and the Local Communities.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you want to be the bridge for JCP and your local community and help us to deploy the Joomla! Certification Program in your area, please apply as Regional Coordinator using the following form: <a href="https://certification.joomla.org/contribute/regional-coordinator">https://certification.joomla.org/contribute/regional-coordinator</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Andrea Gentil (CMT) and Oscar Ortiz (COT) will help with the Regional Coordinators enrollment.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Team planned the first meeting with all the Regional Coordinators for December 12, 2016.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Certification Team is working on a mid-term Plan, defining goals and strategy for the next year.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Community events:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">JoomlaDay Austria with Stefanie Thielmann as Supervisor (December 2, 2016)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Upcoming exam sessions at Joomla! Learning Partners:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Pulsar Informatique - France - November 21, 2016</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr">\r\n<p dir="ltr">Octopoos - France - November 22, 2016</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr">All of these meeting notes are not final and cannot be used as reference.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Meeting ends after 60 minutes.</p>', NULL, 1, 61, 1, 669, '2016-11-17 14:04:04', 0, '2016-11-17 14:04:41', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(375, 0, 32, 'Team Lead Vote, Team Workflow Updates', 'team-lead-vote-team-workflow-updates', '<p>In accordance with the Transition Team\'s directive, the JSST voted to confirm its team lead in accordance with the new project structure voted in May 2015. &nbsp;Of 18 active team members, 15 entered votes and Michael Babker was unanimously selected as the team lead. &nbsp;Voting was conducted from November 5 to November 8. &nbsp;Additional roles will be voted on and filled to satisfy all structure requirements at a later date.</p>\r\n<p>During the last month, the JSST has been reviewing its internal workflows and aiming to improve our workflows and expectations. &nbsp;During this period, we have restored&nbsp;<a href="https://developer.joomla.org/security.html">https://developer.joomla.org/security.html</a>&nbsp;(a page which was unfortunately lost during a previous site upgrade) and have ensured that <a href="https://www.joomla.org/security">https://www.joomla.org/security</a>&nbsp;and <a href="http://security.joomla.org">http://security.joomla.org</a>&nbsp;both direct to this page. &nbsp;The page provides public guidance on the scope of the JSST\'s work, the expectations a reporter can have from the team, and information on how to report an issue (including a public list of GPG keys to enable encrypted communications). &nbsp;We have also updated&nbsp;<a href="https://developer.joomla.org/security-centre.html">https://developer.joomla.org/security-centre.html</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="https://developer.joomla.org/security/contact-the-team.html">https://developer.joomla.org/security/contact-the-team.html</a>&nbsp;to better cross reference this information and make it easier for users to find it and sign up for notifications from our security announcement feed.</p>\r\n<p>We have also streamlined our communication process by transitioning our <a href="mailto:security@joomla.org">security@joomla.org</a>&nbsp;email account to the <a href="https://www.helpscout.net/">Help Scout</a> helpdesk system. &nbsp;This has enabled our team to better receive messages and respond to them.</p>', NULL, 1, 62, 1, 447, '2016-11-17 21:12:54', 0, '2016-11-17 21:25:32', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(376, 0, 53, 'Move from github.io', 'move-from-github-io', '<p>The web master team are rightly complaining we have too many domains. The repository for the <strong>Joomla! en-GB User Interface Text Guidelines </strong>was one of those as it lived in a github pages setup so that we could easiy allow people to submit pull requests and keep the document up to date and relevant.</p>\r\n<p>Using a component (<a href="https://www.flycart.org/index.php/products/joomla/jmarkdown">JMarkdown</a>) we have been able to <em>"live import"</em> the docs from github into the main <a href="https://developer.joomla.org/en-gb-user-interface-text-guidelines.html">https://developer.joomla.org/&nbsp;</a>web site. The documents still live on github so we have all the advantages of pull requests AND the styling of the main web site AND one less domain name.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks to Michael Babker for testing and reviewing the extension and to Ramesh Elamathi for creating the component and responding so quickly to requests for changes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 63, 1, 448, '2016-11-18 21:40:15', 0, '2016-11-18 21:46:08', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(377, 0, 14, 'Transition Changes and policy', 'transition-changes-and-policy', '<p>The VEL team in their recent meeting discussed the transition documents and process.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>"Mandville" was elected by voting member majority to be the new lead and new roles defined for the current members.</p>\r\n<p>New roles for contributors were created.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The API team will be archived and effort concentrated on the help desk and associated works.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 64, 1, 568, '2016-11-19 00:20:41', 0, '2016-11-19 00:22:03', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
