	(423, 0, 14, 'January 2017', 'january-2017', '<p>Here are the points covered by the VEL team in their recent meeting.<br /><br />Discussion on responsible disclosure and time between fixing, release and notification of patch.&nbsp; <br />Discusion on recent and active VEL items.<br />Discussion on vulnerable abandon ware listings.<br />Discussion on SOP manual. <br />Discussion on recent viewing issues caused by server, information given and method of repair.&nbsp; <br />Discussion on social media use. <br />Discussion on transition.<br />Discussion on dedicated VEL tracking extension.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you</p>', NULL, 1, 110, 2, 568, '2017-01-13 20:31:58', 568, '2017-01-18 17:32:54', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(424, 0, 78, 'Certification Steering Meeting - January 17, 2017', 'certification-steering-meeting-january-17-2017', '<p dir="ltr">The Joomla! Certification Steering Group meets every Tuesday at 2:00 PM GMT.<br />This meeting was held on January 17, 2017 on Glip.</p>\r\n<h3>Discussion outline</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Operations team restructured the documents and is ready for 2017. New responsibilities are set up in the group for RC, JUGs and JLPs</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Platform team sorted topics for the sprint in London and depending tickets have been sorted. They received a request for JoomlaDay Florida. The team will improve the flow to buy the seats for JD and JUGs.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Exam Team changed the categories for the questions and fine tuned some questions.</p>\r\n<p>The maintenance system in in development and the structure of data history and version control works on the first glance.</p>\r\n<p>The Certification Team will meet in London during the Joomla! sprint.</p>', NULL, 1, 111, 1, 669, '2017-01-17 17:48:23', 0, '2017-01-17 17:49:18', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(425, 0, 13, '17 January 2017 JUG Team Meeting Minutes', '17-january-2017-jug-team-meeting-minutes', '<p><strong>In attendance:</strong><br />Djamel KherbiBrian Ronnow<br />Rowan Hoskyns-Abrahall<br />Luca Marzo<br />Jenn Gress<br />Eric Lamy</p>\r\n<p><strong>Apologies:</strong><br />Duke Speer</p>\r\n<p><strong>No show:</strong><br />Bruce Valle<br />Daniel Dubois</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Rowan to get our mailing out today.</li>\r\n<li>Listings are all on target.</li>\r\n<li>Rowan to submit the budget by the end of the month.</li>\r\n<li>Jenn to work on docs.joomla.org this week and determine next steps.</li>\r\n<li>Rowan and Jenn to work on a logo for the JUG Team to use in the magazine.</li>\r\n<li>Jenn to start doing the JUG Round Ups for the JCM again.</li>\r\n<li>Adding Certification Exam details to newsletters to open up JUGs to have certification sessions.</li>\r\n<li>Rowan created a new Doodle so we can see what other time options there are for us to meet and get everyone there.</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL, 1, 112, 1, 535, '2017-01-17 20:39:30', 0, '2017-01-17 20:44:03', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(426, 0, 19, 'COT - Meeting notes - January 19, 2017', 'cot-meeting-notes-january-19-2017', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-3cd47ed4-b7dc-24be-6fc7-683346433397" dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.9871999999999999; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: \'Open Sans\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">The Joomla! Certification Operations Team (COT) meets every Thursday at 1:00 PM GMT. This meeting was held on January 19, 2017 on Glip.</span></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.9871999999999999; margin-top: 16pt; margin-bottom: 4pt;"><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: \'Open Sans\'; color: #434343; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Team members</span></h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.9871999999999999; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: \'Open Sans\'; color: #ff9900; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">In attendance</span><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: \'Open Sans\'; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">: Patrick Jungbluth, Oscar Ortiz, Todd Woodward, Richard van Tilborg, Arjen Schrijvers.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.9871999999999999; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13.333333333333332px; font-family: \'Open Sans\'; color: #ff9900; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">Absents</span><span style="font-size: 13